===== Basic-Rental-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>RENTAL AGREEMENT <br/>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Rental Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into on <br/>________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between ________________________, <br/>with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Renter&#8221;</b>) and <br/>________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <br/><b>&#8220;Landlord&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>CONSIDERATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Renter hereby agrees to pay the Landlord the amount of money mentioned in this <br/>Agreement to lease the property owned by the Landlord. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- (Option 1) This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter <br/>referred to as the &#8220;Effective Date&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- (Option 2) Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be <br/>automatically renewed for a new term. <br/></p>
<p><b>PREMISES, USE AND OCCUPANCY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The premises that are to be rented by the Landlord are located at (address) ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- The premises are to be used only for residential purposes and may be occupied only by the <br/>registered occupants.  <br/></p>
<p><b>COSTS AND PAYMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The monthly rent to be paid by the Renter to the Landlord is ________________. It is to be <br/>paid by the Renter before the first day of every month, such that the first rent payment is due <br/>on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- The method of payment preferred by both parties is ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- In the event of late payments made by the Renter, the Landlord is entitled to impose a <br/>________________ fine as late fee.  <br/></p>
<p>- Prior to taking occupancy of the premises, the Renter will pay the Landlord an amount of <br/>________________ as a security deposit to cover the cost of any damages suffered by the <br/>premises and cleaning. Such security deposit will be returned to the Renter upon the end of <br/>this Agreement, provided the premises are left in the same condition as prior to the occupancy. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- This Agreement may be terminated in the event that any of the following occurs: <br/></p>
<p>1. Immediately in the event that one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ABANDONMENT AND THE RIGHT TO ENTER <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that the Renter abandons the premises during the term of this Agreement, the <br/>Landlord will be entitled to enter the Premises by any means without facing any liability and <br/>the Landlord may terminate this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- The Landlord is entitled to enter the premises to inspect or repair the premises. <br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to arbitration/mediation/negotiation (circle one) in accordance with, and subject <br/>to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>PETS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Renter will not keep any pets on the premises without obtaining <br/>written prior consent from the Landlord.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p>RENTER <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>LANDLORD <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>
===== Bookkeeping-Contract-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>BOOKKEEPING CONTRACT <br/>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p><b>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Bookkeeping Contract Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered <br/>into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between <br/>________________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to <br/>as the <b>&#8220;Bookkeeper&#8221;</b>) and ________________, with an address of ________________, <br/>(hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Company&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>SERVICES PROVIDED BY THE BOOKKEEPER <br/></b></p>
<p>The Parties agree that the Bookkeeper will provide the following services to the Company: <br/></p>
<p>1. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>6. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>7. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>8. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>9. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>10. ____________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be automatically renewed <br/>for a new term. <br/></p>
<p><b>SERVICE RATES </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- The Company agrees to compensate the Bookkeeper an amount of ___________ per hour and <br/>the Bookkeeper further agrees to invoice the Company for the total amount of hours worked <br/>at the end of each month.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that in the event that the invoices are not paid within thirty days from receipt, <br/>the Bookkeeper will be entitled to charge a late fee of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN PARTIES  <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties agree that the Bookkeeper in this Agreement is an independent contractor, <br/>where the Bookkeeper provides the services hereunder and acts as an independent contractor.  <br/></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances shall the Bookkeeper be considered an employee.  <br/></p>
<p>- Whereas, this Agreement does not create any other partnership between the Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>PERFORMANCE  <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Bookkeeper hereby consents and promises to perform his/her services to the highest <br/>possible standards.  <br/></p>
<p><b>REPRESENTATION AND WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties declare that they are both fully authorized to enter into this Agreement, <br/>whereby the Bookkeeper is to perform the bookkeeping services in accordance with the ethics <br/>standards set forth by the International Ethics Standards Board for Accountants and any other <br/>applicable rules, laws and regulations. <br/></p>
<p>- All analysis, records, reports, and filings will be performed in compliance with the law.  <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- All terms and conditions of this Agreement and any materials provided during the term of the <br/>Agreement must be kept confidential by the Bookkeeper, unless the disclosure is required <br/>pursuant to process of law.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Bookkeeper will not be entitled to use any information provided to him/her, even after the <br/>conclusion of the Agreement for a period of ________________ years.  <br/></p>
<p>- Disclosing or using this information for any purpose beyond the scope of this Agreement, or <br/>beyond the exceptions set forth above, is expressly forbidden without the prior consent of the <br/>Company. <br/></p>
<p>- This section will remain in force in the event that the Agreement is terminated. <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of, or relating to, this Agreement or the </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>transactions it contemplates (whether for breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action) in the even that such is not related to the direct result of one of the party&#8217;s negligence <br/>or breach. <br/></p>
<p><b>INDEMNITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree not to indemnify and hold one another harmless. This also applies to their <br/>affiliates, agents, officers, employees, and/or successors. The Parties in this Agreement hereby <br/>in addition agree to assign against all (if any) claims, liabilities, damages, losses, penalties, <br/>punitive damages, expenses, any arising reasonable legal fees and/or costs of any kind or any <br/>amount that may arise. This includes, but is not limited to, any amount which may result from <br/>the negligence of, or the breach of, this Agreement by the party that is indemnified, its <br/>successors and assigns that occurs under the terms of this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- This section will remain in full force and tact as well as effect, even upon the termination of <br/>the Agreement naturally, or the early termination by either of the Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in the event that any of the following occurs: <br/></p>
<p>1. Immediately, in the event that one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon termination, the Bookkeeper is required to return all Company content, materials, and <br/>all work products to the Company at his/her earliest convenience, but in no event beyond thirty <br/>(30) days after the date of termination. <br/></p>
<p><b>AUDIT <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Bookkeeper agrees that he/she will maintain full records of all the business <br/>conducted that is relevant to the services in this Agreement and the Agreement itself.  <br/></p>
<p>- The records in the possession of the Bookkeeper will be available for full inspection and audit <br/>by the Company and governmental entities for the period, as required by law. <br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to arbitration/mediation/negotiation (circle one) in accordance with, and subject <br/>to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire Agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof. <br/></p>
<p><b>DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Bookkeeper agrees to complete the bookkeeping services in accordance with the requests <br/>and desires of the Company. However, the Bookkeeper does not warrant that his/her services <br/>will create any additional profits, brand recognition, services or other. Whereas the Parties <br/>further agree that the Bookkeeper is not to be held responsible in the event that his/her services <br/>do not meet the Company&#8217;s desired result.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p>COMPANY <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>BOOKKEEPER <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>
===== Business-Confidentiality-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Business Confidentiality Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This agreement between [Company name] and [Contact name]  is hereby entered into on this date: [Date <br/>here].  <br/></p>
<p>Purpose: [Company name] and [Contact name] will be entering into discussions involving [Company name]'s <br/>development and operation, which require [Company name] to disclose confidential information to [Contact <br/>name] on an ongoing basis. This agreement&#8217;s purpose is to ensure confidentiality and to prevent [Contact <br/>name] from disclosing such confidential information.  <br/></p>
<p>[Company name] and [Contact name] hereby agree to the following: <br/></p>
<p>A: Throughout this agreement, the term &#8220;confidential information&#8221; will refer to any information related to <br/>[Company name] that is generally not known to any third parties, and is owned by [Company name]. <br/>Confidential information includes, but is not limited to:  <br/></p>
<p>1. Product strategies  <br/>2. Finances <br/>3. Contract discussions  <br/>4. Trade secrets  <br/>5. Investing strategies  <br/>6. Marketing strategies  <br/>7. Business plans  <br/>8. Other business affairs of [Company name]  <br/> <br/>B: [Contact name] understands that any intentional or unintentional disclosure of confidential information may <br/>be detrimental to [Company name] and accordingly agrees:  <br/></p>
<p>1. Not to disclose discussions with [Company name] except when required by law  <br/>2. Not to use any confidential information in any way other than for authorized purposes  <br/>3. To maintain confidentiality at all times unless expressly written permission is received from [Company <br/></p>
<p>name] <br/>4. That upon dissolution, all records related to [Company name] will be returned  <br/> <br/>C: The terms outlined above shall not apply when specific information:  <br/></p>
<p>1. Becomes part of public domain  <br/>2. Can be proven to be already owned by [Company name] before signing the agreement  <br/>3. [Company name] expressly gives written permission of disclosure  <br/>4. Is court-ordered for disclosure <br/> <br/>D: Should a court order for disclosure of confidential information be received by [Contact name], [Company <br/>name] must be notified immediately in order to either seek protective orders or waive this agreement according <br/>to the circumstances involved.  <br/> <br/>E: Both parties understand that confidential information is owned by [Company name] and any disclosure of <br/>such to [Contact name] does not convey any manner of license, title or right to this information and may not <br/>appropriate any portion of it for unauthorized uses. <br/></p>
<p>F: Termination of the relationship between [Company name] and [Contact name] does not relieve [Contact <br/>name] and associates of their obligations outlined in this agreement, including the return of all records. <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>G: This agreement shall be governed under the jurisdiction of the state of [State name] <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>Signed:  (company)  Signed:  (contact) <br/>Name of Signatory:   Name of Signatory:  <br/>Date:   Date:  <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>

All sharing of this template must be done using a link to http://www.hloom.com/. For any <br/>questions relating to the use of this template please email us - info@hloom.com <br/></p>

</div></div>

===== Business-Operating-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Business Operating Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This agreement is hereby entered into on this date [Date here] by [First member] and [Second member], for the <br/>purpose of mutually agreeing upon the terms and conditions of the operation of the business [Business name]. <br/> <br/><b>[Business name] <br/></b>[Address line 1 <br/>Address line 2 <br/>Address line 3] <br/>Tel: Telephone number  <br/></p>
<p><b>Organization  <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>The members have formed a business as a [State Name] Limited Liability Company under and pursuant to the <br/>[State Name] Limited Liability Company Act by the filing of Articles of Organization with the Department of the <br/>State of [State Name]. <br/> <br/>1. This agreement is under the jurisdiction of the state of [State name]  <br/>2. The name of the business shall be [Business name] and its members shall conduct business under that <br/></p>
<p>name.  <br/>3. The term of the business shall commence perpetually unless dissolved under the provisions stated in this <br/></p>
<p>agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>Purpose of Company  <br/></b></p>
<p>The business will engage in the following lawful activities:  <br/>1. Repair of computers  <br/>2. Repair of printers  <br/>3. Computer troubleshooting  <br/>4. Installation of computer hardware  <br/></p>
<p><b>Membership  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The members identified in this agreement are the initial members of this business.  <br/>2. The members share ownership and voting interests equally.  <br/>3. Each member shall contribute an initial payment of [Payment amount] to the company upon execution of <br/></p>
<p>the agreement.  <br/>4. The initial members shall approve new members by mutual consent.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Distribution  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. All profits made through the business shall be distributed among members according to their percentage <br/>ownership.  <br/></p>
<p>2. No member may demand or receive distribution in any form besides money.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Transfer of Interests  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. No member shall voluntarily resign from the company until a period of one year has passed from the time <br/>of this agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>2. No member shall receive any return of its capital payment upon their resignation.  <br/>3. No member shall transfer in any manner its interest to another party without having first offered that interest <br/></p>
<p>to the other members via written notice. <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>Records  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The company shall keep accurate and complete accounts on the company's behalf, and the members may <br/>review them at any time.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Disputes  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. In the event of a dispute among members, reasonable effort shall be put forth to meet in person and <br/>resolve the dispute.  <br/></p>
<p>2. If the members fail to resolve a dispute themselves, they shall mutually select a mediator to help them <br/>resolve the dispute.  <br/></p>
<p> <br/>The undersigned affirm that they have read and understood this agreement in its entirety, and hereby agree to <br/>the terms and conditions stated therein: <br/> <br/></p>
<p>   <br/></p>
<p>Date   Date:  <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>
<p><b>Copyright information - Please read</b> <br/>  <br/>&#169; This <b>Free Microsoft Office Template</b> is the copyright of Hloom.com. You can download and modify this template for <br/>your own personal use. You can (and should!) remove this copyright notice (click here to see how) before customizing <br/>the template. <br/>  <br/>You may not distribute or resell this template, or its derivatives, and you may not make it available on other websites <br/>without our prior permission. All sharing of this template must be done using a link to http://www.hloom.com/. For any <br/>questions relating to the use of this template please email us - info@hloom.com <br/></p>

===== Business-Partnership-Agreement (1).html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title>BUSINESS PARTNERSHIP CONTRACT AGREEMENT.docx</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>BUSINESS PARTNERSHIP CONTRACTUAL AGREEMENT<br/>PARTNERS<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Business Partnership Contractual Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the<br/><b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between<br/>________________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred<br/>to as the <b>&#8220;First Partner&#8221;</b>) and ________________with an address of ________________<br/>(hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Second Partner&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Partners&#8221;</b>).<br/></p>
<p><b>PARTNERSHIP PURPOSE<br/></b></p>
<p>The Partners agree that the purpose of this partnership is<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><b>TERM<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the partnership will begin on the date of signing this Agreement and<br/>will continue until its termination.<br/></p>
<p><b>BUSINESS LOCATION<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the location of the business will be at ________________________<br/>and any change to the location of the business will only occur by providing an attached<br/>amendment to this Agreement signed by the Partners.<br/></p>
<p><b>NEW PARTNERS<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that no new partners may be added to this Agreement and partnership.<br/></p>
<p><b>CAPITAL CONTRIBUTIONS<br/></b></p>
<p><b>- </b>The Partners agree to the following capital contributions in case or in property or other<br/>forms of contributions.<br/></p>
<p>Partner Contribution Description Value</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>INTEREST<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that there will be no interest on any capital payment by either of the<br/>partners including any additional capital contributions made.<br/></p>
<p><b>PROFITS AND LOSSES<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the appointed accountants will be responsible to determine the<br/>profits and losses of the partnership.<br/></p>
<p>- The profits and losses will be determined in accordance with the Partners capital<br/>contribution values as examined and deduced by the appointed accountants at the end of<br/>every fiscal year.<br/></p>
<p><b>BORROWING OF PARTNERSHIP INTERESTS<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that no money will be borrowed from the business without the prior<br/>written consent of the other partner.<br/></p>
<p><b>FINANCIALS STATEMENTS<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree to provide a financial statement at the end of every fiscal year showing<br/>the income and expenses of the business indicating and providing each partner&#8217;s share of<br/>the profits.<br/></p>
<p><b>VOTING<br/></b></p>
<p>The Partners agree that their voting weight is determined as follows:<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><b>MANAGEMENT<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the business will be managed as follows:</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><i>Meetings<br/></i></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that meetings will occur at the headquarters of the Partnership or in any<br/>other place as agreed by the Partners.<br/></p>
<p><i>Calling of Meetings<br/></i></p>
<p>- The Partners are entitled to call for a meeting by providing a reasonable notice beforehand.<br/></p>
<p><b>DEATH<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that in case of death of either of the partners, the surviving partner will<br/>be entitled to purchase the interest of the decedent in the partnership from the heirs<br/>and/or assigns.<br/></p>
<p>- The Partners also agree that the surviving partner will be entitled to terminate this<br/>Agreement and partnership.<br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that this Agreement and partnership may be terminated as follows<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS<br/></b>- The Partners agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing where<br/></p>
<p>they must be signed by both Partners to this Agreement.<br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Partners will be applied to this Agreement.<br/><b>SEVERABILITY<br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where a provision of this Agreement is found to be void and/or unenforceable by<br/>a court of competent jurisdiction, then the provisions remaining will continue to be enforced.<br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION</b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>- </b>Any dispute and/or difference arising out of or related to this Agreement will be submitted to<br/>________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) according to, and subject to the laws<br/>of ________________.<br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW<br/></b></p>
<p><b>- </b>This Agreement will be governed by and construed according to the laws of<br/>________________.<br/><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is complete and with respect to the subject matter herein, supersedes all and<br/>any prior agreements, understandings, and conditions, expressed or implied, written or oral,<br/>of any nature with respect to the subject matter herein.<br/></p>
<p>- The expressed terms control and supersede any course of performance and/or usage of the<br/>trade inconsistent with any of the terms herein.<br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such<br/>is demonstrated throughout their signatures below:<br/></p>

===== Business-Partnership-Agreement.html =====

<html><head><title>BUSINESS PARTNERSHIP CONTRACT AGREEMENT.docx</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>BUSINESS PARTNERSHIP CONTRACTUAL AGREEMENT<br/>PARTNERS<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Business Partnership Contractual Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the<br/><b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between<br/>________________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred<br/>to as the <b>&#8220;First Partner&#8221;</b>) and ________________with an address of ________________<br/>(hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Second Partner&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Partners&#8221;</b>).<br/></p>
<p><b>PARTNERSHIP PURPOSE<br/></b></p>
<p>The Partners agree that the purpose of this partnership is<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><b>TERM<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the partnership will begin on the date of signing this Agreement and<br/>will continue until its termination.<br/></p>
<p><b>BUSINESS LOCATION<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the location of the business will be at ________________________<br/>and any change to the location of the business will only occur by providing an attached<br/>amendment to this Agreement signed by the Partners.<br/></p>
<p><b>NEW PARTNERS<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that no new partners may be added to this Agreement and partnership.<br/></p>
<p><b>CAPITAL CONTRIBUTIONS<br/></b></p>
<p><b>- </b>The Partners agree to the following capital contributions in case or in property or other<br/>forms of contributions.<br/></p>
<p>Partner Contribution Description Value</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>INTEREST<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that there will be no interest on any capital payment by either of the<br/>partners including any additional capital contributions made.<br/></p>
<p><b>PROFITS AND LOSSES<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that the appointed accountants will be responsible to determine the<br/>profits and losses of the partnership.<br/></p>
<p>- The profits and losses will be determined in accordance with the Partners capital<br/>contribution values as examined and deduced by the appointed accountants at the end of<br/>every fiscal year.<br/></p>
<p><b>BORROWING OF PARTNERSHIP INTERESTS<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that no money will be borrowed from the business without the prior<br/>written consent of the other partner.<br/></p>
<p><b>FINANCIALS STATEMENTS<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree to provide a financial statement at the end of every fiscal year showing<br/>the income and expenses of the business indicating and providing each partner&#8217;s share of<br/>the profits.<br/></p>
<p><b>VOTING<br/></b></p>
<p>The Partners agree that their voting weight is determined as follows:<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>

<p>- The Partners agree that the business will be managed as follows:</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><i>Meetings<br/></i></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that meetings will occur at the headquarters of the Partnership or in any<br/>other place as agreed by the Partners.<br/></p>
<p><i>Calling of Meetings<br/></i></p>
<p>- The Partners are entitled to call for a meeting by providing a reasonable notice beforehand.<br/></p>
<p><b>DEATH<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Partners agree that in case of death of either of the partners, the surviving partner will<br/>be entitled to purchase the interest of the decedent in the partnership from the heirs<br/>and/or assigns.<br/></p>
<p>- The Partners also agree that the surviving partner will be entitled to terminate this<br/>Agreement and partnership.<br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION<br/></b></p>

===== Commercial-Tenancy-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Commercial Tenancy Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/><b>Parties to the Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>Landlord  Tenant  <br/>Address  Address  <br/>    <br/>Address of Property  <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>Term for which the property is leased <br/></b> <br/>From and including  20  <br/>To and including  20  <br/></p>
<p>In the event the tenant is more than one person, each tenant will be equally responsible for the rental payments.  <br/></p>
<p>Parking: No more than 60 vehicles may be parked on the property. <br/></p>
<p>Rent: $3,500.00 per month subject to increase at the end of this commercial tenancy agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>First Payment Date: August 1, 2013. <br/></p>
<p>Monthly Payment Date: Monthly rent payments are due on the 1st day of each month. Rent payments made after <br/>the 5th day of each month are subject to a 3% late fee each day following the 5th day of the month.  <br/></p>
<p>The landlord is entitled to recover late fees. <br/></p>
<p>The Landlord, at his own expense, shall furnish the following utilities or amenities for the benefit of the Tenant: <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>The Tenant, at his own expense, shall furnish the following: <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>Deposit $2,000 + first month&#8217;s rent. <br/>Rent is subject to increase upon renewal of lease. <br/>The landlord is entitled to keep the tenant&#8217;s deposit should the tenant move out before the lease has expired. The <br/>landlord shall give 30 days&#8217; notice should the renter be required to move before the lease has expired.  <br/>The property is leased to the tenant(s) for 1 year and a rent review will be scheduled 1 year from the date this <br/>agreement is signed to determine lease renewal.  <br/>The landlord is responsible for maintaining the structure of the building including, but not limited to, walls, yards, <br/>roads, parking lots, paths, gutters, drains, wires, cables, sewers and pipes, in a manner that is in keeping with local <br/>building codes and government safety regulations.  <br/>The tenant is responsible for charges incurred should the tenant break the lease before the contract time has expired <br/>or, if at the end of the term of the lease, the property is not in the same condition or repair as it was when the lease <br/>began.  <br/>The tenant is not permitted by the terms of this contract to sublet the property to another party. <br/> <br/>Signed this [________] day of [_________________], [Year] <br/> <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Landlord  Tenant  Witness <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>

<p>A. There is damage to on site property. <br/>B. Services were done incorrectly/problem is not fixed. <br/>C. The computer or software is no longer functioning during or after service.  <br/></p>
<p>[ABC Computers] is to provide the following services for a term of [_____] [days/months/years]: Software <br/>updating, computer virus protection, computer maintenance, computer software bug fixes, computer upgrade <br/>requirements, computer software problem shooting, laptop virus protection, laptop maintenance, laptop <br/>upgrade requirements, and laptop software problem shooting. [ABC Computers] will send a computer <br/>technician to [Customer] within 24 hours of being contacted about service needs. If [ABC Computers] does not <br/>resolve the computer issue within that time, all services provided for THAT 24 HOUR PERIOD shall be <br/>charged at [_____]% off of the original price.  <br/></p>
<p>[Customer] agrees to pay $[Amount] to [ABC Computers] for the service of [_______________ <br/>_______________________________________________________________________________________]. <br/></p>
<p>[Customer] has [______] computers on site. [ABC Computers] will be servicing [______] computers on site. <br/>Payment of services is made out to [ABC Computers].  <br/></p>
<p>[ABC Computers] and [Customer] hereby agree to the term of [________] [days/months/years] for services <br/>rendered. Any services provided beyond the date of [DATE] shall require the drafting of a new service <br/>agreement. <br/></p>

<p><b>[ABC Computers] <br/></b></p>

<p>Title:  <br/></p>

===== Employment-Contract-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT <br/>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p><b>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Employment Contract Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered <br/>into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between <br/>________________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred to <br/>as the <b>&#8220;Employer&#8221;</b>), and ________________, with an address of ________________ <br/>(hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Employee&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- During the employment period, the Employee shall have the responsibility to perform the <br/>following duties: <br/></p>
<p>1. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>6. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>7. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>8. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>9. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>10. ________________________________ <br/> <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any responsibilities provided in this Agreement may not be assigned to <br/>any other party unless both parties agree to the assignment in writing. <br/></p>
<p><b>PAY AND COMPENSATION</b> <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that the Employer will pay the Employee an annual salary of <br/>________________ payable semi-monthly and subject to regular deductions and withholdings <br/>as required by law. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>
<p>- Whereas the Parties also agree that annual salary may be increased annually by an amount as <br/>may be approved by the Employer and, upon such increase, the increased amount shall <br/>thereafter be deemed to be the annual salary for purposes of this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>BENEFITS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that the Employee shall receive the benefits (Insurance, Holiday and <br/>Vacation) provided by the Employer as indicated below.<b> <br/></b></p>
<p>1. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. ________________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b>WORKING HOURS AND LOCATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Employee agrees that he/she will be working from ________________to <br/>________________ (Monday to Friday), with a ________________lunch break.  <br/></p>
<p>- In particular, the Employee agrees that he/she will work on average ________________ <br/>hours per week. <br/></p>
<p>- The Employee&#8217;s place of work shall be located in ________________ or such other location <br/>as the Parties may agree upon from time to time. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMs OF AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be automatically <br/>renewed for a new term. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in case the following occurs: <br/></p>
<p>1. Immediately in case one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing a written notice to the other party ________________ <br/>days prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon terminating this Agreement, the Employee will be required to return all Employer&#8217;s <br/>materials, products or any other content at his/her earliest convenience, but not beyond <br/>________________ days.  <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY  </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- All terms and conditions of this Agreement and any materials provided during the term of the <br/>Agreement must be kept confidential by the Employee, unless the disclosure is required <br/>pursuant to process of law.  <br/></p>
<p>- Disclosing or using this information for any purpose beyond the scope of this Agreement, or <br/>beyond the exceptions set forth above, is expressly forbidden without the prior consent of the <br/>Employer. <br/></p>
<p><b>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Employee agrees that any intellectual property provided to him/her by the <br/>Employer will remain the sole property of the Employer including, but not limited to, <br/>copyrights, patents, trade secret rights, and other intellectual property rights associated with <br/>any ideas, concepts, techniques, inventions, processes, works of authorship, Confidential <br/>Information or trade secrets.   <br/></p>
<p><b>EXCLUSIVITY </b> <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that this Agreement is not an exclusive arrangement and that the Employer <br/>is entitled to enter into other similar agreements with other employees.  <br/></p>
<p>- However, the Employee is not entitled to enter into a similar agreement as long as he/she <br/>remains a party to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In no event shall the Employer nor the Employee be individually liable for any damages for <br/>breach of duty by third parties, unless the Employer&#8217;s or Employee&#8217;s act or failure to act <br/>involves intentional misconduct, fraud, or a knowing violation of the law. <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW</b> <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to ________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) in accordance with, <br/>and subject to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ATTORNEY FEES  </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- In the event of any dispute between the parties concerning the terms and provisions of this <br/>Agreement, the party prevailing in such dispute shall be entitled to collect from the other party <br/>all costs incurred in such dispute, including reasonable attorneys&#8217; fees. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated throughout by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>EMPLOYEE <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>EMPLOYER <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b> <br/></b></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>
===== Equipment-Lease-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Equipment Lease Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This agreement is to establish the terms of the rental of a steam cleaning device (the device) and is hereby entered into on <br/>this date [Date here] by [Lessor name] and [Lessee name]. <br/> <br/><b>Lessor: </b> <b>Lessee:  <br/>[Lessor name]  <br/></b>[Address line 1 <br/>Address line 2 <br/>Address line 3] <br/>Tel: [Telephone number]  <br/></p>
<p> <b>[Lessee name] <br/></b>[Address line 1 <br/>Address line 2 <br/>Address line 3] <br/>Tel: [Telephone number] <br/></p>
<p> <br/>The lessor and lessee agree to the following terms and conditions: <br/></p>
<p><b>Lease  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The lessee is renting one professional steam cleaning device. <br/>2. The term of lease will begin on August 1, 2014, and conclude on August 14, 2014.  <br/>3. The rental fee of $50.00 will be paid in one installment by the lessee at the time of the rental.  <br/>4. A deposit of $25.00 will be paid by the lessee prior to the rental. This deposit will be returned to the lessee conditional <br/></p>
<p>after concluding the rental, upon the lessee's adherence to the terms of this agreement.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Obligations  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The lessee will use the device in a proper manner, complying with all applicable laws and ordinances which may in <br/>any way relate to the possession or use of the device.  <br/></p>
<p>2. The lessee is responsible for keeping the device in good repair and in working order at their own expense, including <br/>furnishing any parts required to repair the device during the rental term.  <br/></p>
<p>3. The lessee will assume all risks of loss or damage caused to the device. No loss or damage caused to the device will <br/>cause the rest of this agreement to become void.  <br/></p>
<p>4. At the end of the rental agreement, the lessee will return the device to the lessor in good condition, normal wear from <br/>proper usage excepted.  <br/></p>
<p>5. The return of the device shall be at the lessee's expense to the address of the lessor provided.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Liability  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The lessee releases the lessor from any liability due to expenses, damages, or injury caused by the rental and usage of <br/>the device.  <br/></p>
<p>2. The device shall at all times remain the property of the lessor.  <br/>3. This agreement will be governed under the jurisdiction of the state of [State name] <br/> <br/>The undersigned have read this agreement and consent to abide by its terms therein: <br/> <br/></p>
<p>Lessor: [Lessor name]  Lessee: [Lessee name] <br/></p>
<p>Name of Signatory:   Signature:  <br/></p>
<p>Signature:   Date:  <br/></p>
<p>Date:     <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>

All sharing of this template must be done using a link to http://www.hloom.com/. For any <br/>questions relating to the use of this template please email us - info@hloom.com <br/></p>

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>EVENT PLANNING CONTRACT <br/>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This event planning contract (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Contract&#8221;</b>) is entered into on <br/>________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between ________________________, <br/>with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Client&#8221;</b>) and <br/>________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <br/><b>&#8220;Planner&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>EVENT BACKGROUND <br/></b></p>
<p>- The event will take place on ________________, on which date(s) the Client plans to hold the <br/>event described below: <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b>PLANNER DUTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Client hereby engages the Planner to perform the following duties relevant to the event: <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>____________ <br/></p>
<p>- The Planner is required to obtain written consent from the Client prior to entering into any <br/>contractual agreements or issuing deposits or invoices.  <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENTS</b> <br/></p>
<p>- The Client hereby agrees to pay the Planner an amount of ________________ for the services <br/>performed. <br/></p>
<p>- The Planner will provide an invoice at the time of the payment.  <br/></p>
<p><b>CANCELLATION POLICY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Client is entitled to cancel this Contract at any given time. <br/></p>
<p>- The Client is entitled to a full refund in the event that he/she cancels ________________ days <br/>before the beginning of the event.  <br/></p>
<p>- In the event that the Client cancels less than ________________ days before the beginning of <br/>the event, he/she will not be entitled to a refund. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- The Planner is entitled to cancel this Contract at any given time. <br/></p>
<p>- In the event of cancellation by the Planner, he/she is required to provide a replacement planner <br/>that the Client agrees to. In this case, the Planner will be required to refund any money <br/>previously provided by the Client as a budget for the event or other.  <br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION ALTERNATIVES <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of, or in connection with, this Contract shall <br/>be submitted to arbitration/mediation/negotiation (circle one) in accordance with, and subject <br/>to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>LEGAL FEES <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event of a dispute that results in legal action, the successful party will be entitled to the <br/>legal fees, such as attorney&#8217;s fees or other.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY  <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Contract is found to be void and unenforceable by a court <br/>of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in accordance <br/>with the Parties&#8217; intention.  <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Contract contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties to it with <br/>respect to its subject matter, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, inducements <br/>and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with respect to its <br/>subject matter. The express terms of the Contract control and supersede any course of <br/>performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of its terms.  <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Contract shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Contract and such is <br/>demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>CLIENT <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>PLANNER <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ </p>

</div></div>

===== General-Partnership-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>General Partnership Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>[PARTNER #1 NAME], residing at the address [PARTNER #1 ADDRESS], and [PARTNER #2 NAME], <br/>residing at the address [PARTNER #2 ADDRESS], referred to as &#8220;The Partners&#8221;, agree to the following terms <br/>and conditions: <br/> <br/>The Partners agree to establish themselves as equal partners of the business of [BAKERY AND CAFE]. The <br/>Partners agree that the business shall be hereinafter named [________________________]. The business is <br/>located at [BUSINESS ADDRESS] in the State of [STATE NAME]. <br/> <br/>The Partners agree to pay  <br/> <br/></p>
<p>&#61623; the amount of $[AMOUNT]  <br/>&#61623; to the bank of [BANK NAME] located at [BANK ADDRESS] <br/>&#61623; by [DATE] / in the month of [MONTH], in the year [________]  <br/>&#61623; to an account set up in the name of the business [BUSINESS NAME].  <br/></p>
<p> <br/>The Partners agree to pay an equal amount. <br/> <br/>The Partners agree that [____________________________] shall maintain the title of [__________________] <br/>within the business. The Partners agree to the equal distribution of profits gained from the business. Any <br/>assets contributed to the business by either Partner shall remain the property of that Partner.  <br/> <br/>The Partners agree that the partnership will commence on [DATE] and will continue until [DATE] or until both <br/>Partners agree to dissolve the partnership on mutual terms. <br/> <br/>The Partners agree that they will both maintain equal standings within the business. No partner shall determine <br/>any course of action for the business without the express agreement of the other Partner. The Partnership will <br/>be maintained by devoting an equal amount of time and effort by both Partners. No Partner shall exceed <br/>spending of more than $[AMOUNT] without the express agreement of the other Partner. <br/> <br/>The undersigned agree to all of the terms and conditions of this [PARTNERSHIP AGREEMENT], pertaining to <br/>the business [BUSINESS NAME]. <br/> <br/>On this the [_________] day of the month of [_________________], in the year [_______], I, [NAME OF <br/>PARTNER #1] agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this [PARTNERSHIP AGREEMENT]. <br/> <br/> <br/>Partner Signature: ___________________________________  <br/> <br/>On this the [_________] day of the month of [_________________], in the year [_______], I, [NAME OF <br/>PARTNER #2] agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this [PARTNERSHIP AGREEMENT]. <br/> <br/> <br/>Partner Signature: ___________________________________  <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/> <br/></p>
<p>   <br/>Witness Name  Witness Signature <br/></p>
<p> <br/>  </p>

<p>4. ________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ________________________________________________________________________ </p>

</div></div>

<p>7. ________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>8. ________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>9. ________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>

<p><b>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree on the following points. <br/></p>
<p>1. The Indemnified Party will be indemnified from any claims, judgements, actions or otherwise <br/>when it comes to the costs of attorney/defense fees related to the agreement between the <br/>Parties. This extends to the Indemnifying Party&#8217;s representatives, agents, employees and more.  <br/></p>
<p>2. In case any claim arises in consideration with the scope of this Agreement, the Indemnifying <br/>Party will have to pay for the Indemnified Party&#8217;s counsel chosen by the Indemnified Party <br/>himself/herself.  <br/></p>
<p>3. ___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. ___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>

<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW</b> <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to ________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) (Circle one) in <br/>accordance with, and subject to the laws of, ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>REPRESENTATION AND WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree and disclose that they are authorized fully for entering this Agreement. Both <br/>Parties&#8217; performances and obligations are not to violate the rights of any third party or else <br/>violate other, if any, agreements made between them and/or any other organization, person, <br/>business or law/governmental regulation.  <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of or relating to this Agreement or the <br/>transactions it contemplates (whether for breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action) in case such is not related to the direct result of one party&#8217;s negligence or breach. <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated throughout by their signatures below: <br/></p>

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>INDEPENDENT CONTRACT <br/>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p><b>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Independent Contract Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered <br/>into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between <br/>________________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to <br/>as the <b>&#8220;Client&#8221;</b>) and ________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter <br/>referred to as the <b>&#8220;Contractor&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>GENERAL <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Client agrees that the Contractor possesses the relevant experience, necessary <br/>qualifications and abilities to provide services to the Client.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SERVICES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The duties of the Contractor towards the Client are listed below: <br/></p>
<p>1. ___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. ___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. ___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. ___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ___________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b>COMPENSATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties Agree that the Client will compensate the Contractor through the following means: <br/></p>
<p>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________<br/>______________________________________________________________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) <br/>and will terminate upon the completion of the provision of the services set forth in this <br/>Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be prolonged only on written confirmation provided by both Parties. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that this Agreement is an independent contractor agreement where the <br/>Contractor provides the specified services and acts as an independent contractor.  <br/></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances shall the independent contractor be considered an employee.  <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement does not create any other partnership between the Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY  <br/></b></p>
<p>- All terms and conditions of this Agreement and any materials provided during the term of the <br/>Agreement must be kept confidential by the Contractor, unless the disclosure is required <br/>pursuant to process of law.  <br/></p>
<p>- Disclosing or using this information for any purpose beyond the scope of this Agreement, or <br/>beyond the exceptions set forth above, is expressly forbidden without the prior consent of the <br/>Client. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in the event that any of the following occurs:  <br/></p>
<p>1. Immediately in the event that one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon terminating this Agreement, the Client will be responsible for paying  for all the services <br/>provided by the Contractor until the day of termination, unless it is the Contractor who breaches <br/>this Agreement, where he/she fails to rectify such breach upon reasonable notice. <br/></p>
<p><b>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Contractor agrees that any intellectual property provided to him/her by the Client will <br/>remain the sole property of the Client, including, but not limited to, copyrights, patents, trade <br/>secret rights, and other intellectual property rights associated with any ideas, concepts, <br/>techniques, inventions, processes, works of authorship, confidential information or trade <br/>secrets.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- Accordingly, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of or relating to this Agreement or the <br/>transactions it contemplates (whether for breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action) in the event that such is not related to the direct result of one of the Parties&#8217; negligence <br/>or breach. <br/></p>
<p><b>LEGAL FEES <br/></b></p>

===== Intellectual-Property-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"

<html><head><title></title>

</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY <br/>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p><b>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Intellectual Property Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered <br/>into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between <br/>________________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred to <br/>as the <b>&#8220;Employee&#8221;</b>), and ________________, with an address of ________________ <br/>(hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Employer&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that the Employee assigns the Employer all the present and future <br/>rights and title, as well as the interest to all intellectual property (hereinafter referred to as <br/>&#8220;<b>Intellectual Property</b>&#8221;) that is created and/or discovered during the term of their <br/>employment.  <br/></p>
<p>- Intellectual Property includes, but is not limited to, trademarks, trade names, service marks, <br/>service mark registrations, service names, patents, patent rights, copyrights, inventions, <br/>licenses, approvals, governmental authorizations, trade secrets, algorithms, codes, inventions, <br/>processes, software, formulas, ideas, concepts and developments.  <br/></p>
<p><b>PRIOR INVENTIONS</b> <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that any Intellectual Property that has already been in existence <br/>prior to the employment of the Employee will remain the exclusive property of the Employee <br/>in case the Employee has a right, title, or interest in it.  <br/></p>
<p>- The prior inventions of the Employee are enlisted below: <br/></p>
<p>1. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>6. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>7. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>8. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>9. _____________________________ </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>10. _____________________________ <br/></p>
<p><b>PATENT AND COPYRIGHT REGISTRATIONS <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Employee agrees that he/she will cooperate with the Employer in this Agreement <br/>as reasonably as possible for the sake of obtaining the copyrights and patents that are needed <br/>for the security of the Employer&#8217;s ownership rights in the Intellectual Property. This <br/>cooperation will last during the course of the employment as well as after its termination.  <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement will begin on _____________________________ and will remain in effect <br/>until _____________________________. <br/></p>
<p>- After the termination of this Agreement, the Employer will acquire exclusive ownership <br/>rights to all the Employee&#8217;s post-employment intellectual property that arises from or relates <br/>to his/her work for the Employer in this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>RETURN OF DATA AND DOCUMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that after the termination of this Agreement the Employee will return all <br/>the tangible embodiments of the Intellectual Property immediately as per the orders of the <br/>Employer. Such include, but are not limited to drawings, documents, data and notes that are <br/>or have been developed during the course of the employment.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Employee hereby agrees not to make any copies of the tangible embodiments or try to <br/>recreate them. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree not to assign the responsibilities in this Agreement to any third party <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW</b> <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>SUCCESSORS AND ASSIGNS  <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that this Agreement will bind upon the Employee&#8217;s heirs, successors and <br/>assigns for the sake of the benefit of the Employer and the Employer&#8217;s heirs, successors and <br/>assigns. <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated throughout by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>

===== Internal-Service-Level-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Internal Service Level Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/><b>Purpose:</b> This agreement defines the roles and responsibilities of [Company name]'s [Department name] in <br/>support of [Company name]'s mission.  <br/> <br/>Scope of Service: [Company name]'s [Department name] facilitates and supports the everyday operation of <br/>[Company name] through its computer system.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Services Offered:  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. Regular backups of systems and applications <br/>2. A troubleshooting program for software and hardware issues  <br/>3. Data recovery  <br/>4. Operational support for existing technology  <br/>5. Support for standard software applications, such as installations  <br/>6. Technical support employees on staff during working hours to answer questions and perform <br/></p>
<p>troubleshooting  <br/></p>
<p><b>Maintenance Schedules  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The standard schedule for non-emergency system maintenance will be Sunday, 12:00 PM through <br/>Monday, 4:00 AM.  <br/></p>
<p>2. Emergency maintenance schedules will be on a case-by-case basis, subject to review and agreed upon by <br/>affected departments.  <br/></p>
<p>3. Daily staffed support will be available in the office Monday through Friday, 8:00 AM through 5:00 PM.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Agreement Terms  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The signatures below indicate that this agreement has been read and is understood, and represents the <br/>proper Technical Support scope of services.  <br/></p>
<p>2. This agreement is subject to the approval, review and enforcement of Mr. Gregory Wheeler, senior director <br/>of the Technical Support department and Ms. Elaine Brown, manager of [Company name].  <br/></p>
<p>3. Any modification or termination of this agreement will require appropriate review and approval by both <br/>parties.  <br/></p>
<p>4. This agreement will be reviewed annually at the beginning of each year to verify its currency and accuracy.  <br/>5. Any input, questions or concerns regarding this agreement should be brought to the senior director of the <br/></p>
<p>Technical Support department for review. <br/></p>
<p><b>Approval  <br/></b></p>
<p>The undersigned hereby understand and agree to the terms of this agreement. <br/> <br/></p>
<p>[Department name]  [Company name] <br/></p>
<p>Name of Signatory:   Name of Signatory:  <br/></p>
<p>Date:   Date:  <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>

===== Limited-Liability-Operating-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"

<html><head><title></title>
