<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Limited Liability Operating Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This [AGREEMENT] hereby acknowledges the formation of [ABC LLC], on this the [______] day of the month <br/>of [____________] in the year [______], in accordance to [STATE NAME] State laws and Federal laws. The <br/>members, or owners, of [ABC LLC] hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this agreement in <br/>accordance to the company guidelines set forth by [ABC LLC]. The undersigned agree to the following <br/>conditions: <br/> <br/>The members, or owners, of [ABC LLC] shall actively participate in the operation of the [LIMITED LIABILITY <br/>COMPANY]. The undersigned agree to establish a set of rules and regulations within the company concerning <br/>profit gain and distribution. The distribution of profits shall be determined by the share of ownership dictated by <br/>the percentage of initial investment. Any change in initial start up investment shall be determined by the <br/>company guidelines created by [ABC LLC].  <br/> <br/>In the instance that any member, or owner, chooses to terminate his or her participation with [ABC LLC], the <br/>undersigned agree to fairly distribute any profits, losses, or assets in accordance to the initial investment <br/>percentage. <br/> <br/>The undersigned agree to form a Managerial System within [ABC LLC]. The members, or owners, of the <br/>[LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY] agree to have [______________________________] serve as acting <br/>manager of [ABC LLC]. The above-mentioned managerial candidate will act in accordance the company <br/>guidelines and [STATE NAME] State laws. The above-mentioned managerial candidate will also function in full <br/>cooperation with the undersigned members, or owners.  <br/> <br/>The undersigned agree to all of the terms and conditions set forth in this [AGREEMENT]. <br/> <br/></p>

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Management Service Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p>[XYZ CREDENTIALS] located at [XYZ CREDENTIALS&#8217; ADDRESS] in the State of [STATE NAME] and [JOE <br/>FITZGERALD], located at [JOE FITZGERALD&#8217;S ADDRESS] in the State of [STATE NAME] hereby enter into <br/>this [AGREEMENT]: <br/></p>
<p>Services provided shall include the following: Management of [XYZ CREDENTIALS&#8217;] finances, management of <br/>[XYZ CREDENTIALS&#8217;] employees, management of all company press releases and events, and management <br/>of [XYZ CREDENTIALS&#8217;] daily operations. Daily operations are to be stipulated within the company guidelines. <br/>[JOE FITZGERALD] shall be required to inform [XYZ CREDENTIALS] of all necessary supplies and equipment <br/>needed to perform his duties to the best of his abilities. [JOE FITZGERALD] is required to maintain daily <br/>contact with the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer of [XYZ CREDENTIALS]. <br/></p>
<p>[JOE FITZGERALD] has a resume with a background focused on [________________], [________________], <br/>and agrees to offer [XYZ CREDENTIALS] his expertise in these fields. By signing below, [JOE FITZGERALD] <br/>agrees to perform his duties to the best of his abilities. <br/></p>
<p>The undersigned agree to the following payment for services rendered: <br/></p>
<p>[JOE FITZGERALD] is to receive a salary of $[SALARY AMOUNT] per year. [JOE FITZGERALD] is to read <br/>and sign a company-drafted contract for the term of [____] years. If [XYZ CREDENTIALS] believes the <br/>services rendered to be unsatisfactory in accordance to the company guidelines, this agreement shall become <br/>null and void. If [JOE FITZGERALD] wishes to terminate his relationship with [XYZ CREDENTIALS] before the <br/>date of [DATE], his severance pay is to be $[AMOUNT] or the amount stipulated further within his contract. <br/></p>
<p>The undersigned agree to all of the terms and conditions stipulated in this [AGREEMENT]. <br/></p>
<p><b>[XYZ Credentials]: <br/></b></p>

<p>Title:  <br/></p>

===== Marketing-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>MARKETING AGREEMENT <br/>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Marketing Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into on <br/>________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>) by and between ________________________ <br/>(hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Client&#8221;</b>) with an address of ________________ and <br/>________________ (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Marketer&#8221;</b>) with an address of <br/>________________ (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>SERVICES PROVIDED <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Marketer agrees to provide the services enlisted below (hereinafter referred to as <br/>the &#8220;<b>Services</b>&#8221;): <br/></p>
<p>1. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>6. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>7. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>8. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>The Parties agree that the Services must be completed by <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENT AND FEES</b> <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the total cost of the Services will be ____________. <br/></p>
<p>- More specifically,  ____________ will be paid at the signing of this Agreement, and <br/>____________ will be paid at completion. <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Marketer will provide an invoice to the Client every ____________ <br/>days upon the completion of the Services. <br/></p>
<p>- The Marketer agrees to obtain consent from the Client prior to making the purchase if  an <br/>expense is over ____________. <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the means of payment will be via <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;). It will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated if the following occurs: <br/></p>
<p>1. This Agreement will be terminated immediately if one of the Parties breaches this <br/>Agreement. More specifically, Iit will also be terminated if one of the Parties breaches a <br/>condition set forth in this Agreement without amending it within a period of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p>2. This Agreement can be terminated at any given time by providing a written notice to the <br/>other party ________________ days prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>3. This Agreement will automatically be terminated when both Parties complete their <br/>obligations. <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY  <br/></b></p>
<p>- All terms and conditions of this Agreement (and any confidential information provided by the <br/>Client to the Marketer or vice versa) during the term of the Agreement must be kept <br/>confidential, unless the disclosure is required pursuant to process of law.  <br/></p>
<p>- Disclosing or using this information for any purpose beyond the scope of this Agreement (or <br/>beyond the exceptions set forth above) is expressly forbidden without the prior consent of the <br/>Parties. <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties&#8217; obligation to maintain confidentiality will survive termination of this Agreement <br/>and remain in effect indefinitely. <br/></p>
<p><b>RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN PARTIES  <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties agree that the Marketer in this Agreement is an independent contractor, as <br/>he/she provides the services hereunder and acts as an independent contractor.<b> <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Marketer shall not be considered an employee under any circumstances. <b> <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement does not create any other partnership between the Parties.<b> <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is an Agreement that is not based on exclusivity. Hence, the Parties are <br/>entitled to enter into other Agreements with other parties.<b> <br/></b></p>
<p><b>OWNERSHIP <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that all products created by the Marketer will remain the exclusive property <br/>of the Client, as long as it is relevant to the performance of the Services set forth in this <br/>Agreement. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Marketer agrees that any intellectual property provided to him/her by the Client will <br/>remain the sole property of the Client, including (but not limited to) copyrights, patents, trade <br/>secret rights, and other intellectual property rights associated with any ideas, concepts, <br/>techniques, inventions, processes, works of authorship, Confidential Information, or trade <br/>secrets. <br/></p>
<p>- The Marketer will refrain from using such intellectual property upon the termination of this <br/>Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of or relating to this Agreement or the <br/>transactions it contemplates (including breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action)&#8212;if said damage is the direct result of one of the party&#8217;s negligence or breach. <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be made in writing and <br/>signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree not to assign any of the responsibilities in this Agreement to a third <br/>party unless consented by both Parties in writing.  <br/></p>
<p><b>ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to ________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) (Circle one), in <br/>accordance with and subject to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto, <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof. It supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements, and conditions (express, implied, oral, written, or of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof). The express terms hereof control and supersede any <br/>course of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event when any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, the remaining provisions will still be enforced, in accordance <br/>with the Parties&#8217; intention.  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement. This <br/>agreement is demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p>MARKETER <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>CLIENT <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>

The undersigned members agree to actively participate within the <br/>company and complete their tasks in accordance with the company&#8217;s guidelines, as well as [STATE NAME] <br/>State law. In the case that a new <br/>member is joining [XYZ LLC], this agreement shall be redrafted in accordance to all of the wishes of the <br/>members. <br/> <br/>The undersigned agree to meet all of the terms within the company guidelines as well as within this document. <br/> <br/></p>

<p><b>GOVERNING LAW</b> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to ________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) (Circle one) in <br/>accordance with, and subject to the laws of, ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing and  they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree not to assign any of the responsibilities in this Agreement to a third <br/>party unless consented to by both Parties in writing.  <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, <br/>understandings, inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any <br/>nature whatsoever with respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control <br/>and supersede any course of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of <br/>the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>REPRESENTATION AND WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree and disclose that they are authorized fully for entering this Agreement. Both <br/>Parties&#8217; performances and obligations are not to violate the rights of any third party or else <br/>violate other, if any, agreements made between them and/or any other organization, person, <br/>business or law/governmental regulation.  <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of or relating to this Agreement or the <br/>transactions it contemplates (whether for breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action) in case such is not related to the direct result of one Party&#8217;s negligence or breach. <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated throughout by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p> <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>
===== Mutual-Confidentiality-Agreement (1).html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Mutual Confidentiality Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This agreement is hereby entered into by [Name of first party] and [Name of second party] on this date: <br/>[Date here]. <br/> <br/><b>Purpose:</b> To protect the information shared between [Name first party] and [Name second party] against <br/>any unauthorized usage or disclosure. <br/> <br/>The parties hereby agree to the following:  <br/> <br/>A: Throughout the agreement, &#8220;confidential information&#8221; refers to information owned by the disclosing <br/>parties and generally not known to third parties. It may include information relating to these subjects:  <br/> <br/>1. Product strategies <br/>2. Site location strategies  <br/>3. Contract discussions  <br/>4. Pricing Policies  <br/>5. Marketing information  <br/>6. Business plans  <br/>7. Technical knowledge  <br/>8. Financing strategies  <br/>9. Trade secrets  <br/>10. Investing strategies  <br/>11. Other business affairs of the disclosing parties  <br/> <br/>B: All information disclosed to a receiving party shall be treated as confidential and therefore under the <br/>terms of this agreement.  <br/> <br/>C: Both parties understand that any intentional or unintentional unauthorized usage or disclosure of <br/>confidential information may be detrimental to the disclosing party and is in violation of this agreement. <br/>Each party agrees to the following:  <br/> <br/>1. Not to use confidential information in any way that deviates from authorized purpose.  <br/>2. Not to disclose the object and scope of any discussions between the parties, except where required by <br/></p>
<p>law.  <br/>3. Not to disclose confidential information to any third party without written consent of the disclosing <br/></p>
<p>party.  <br/>4. That upon termination of the partnership, all records pertaining to confidential information be returned <br/></p>
<p>to the disclosing party.  <br/> <br/>D: The obligations outlined above shall not apply to material that:  <br/> <br/>1. Through no act of the receiving party becomes part of public domain  <br/>2. Can be proven to be owned by the receiving party before this agreement  <br/>3. Is disclosed by court order  <br/>4. Is authorized for release in writing by the disclosing party.  <br/> <br/>E: Should the receiving party receive a court order to turn over any confidential information, the disclosing <br/>party must be immediately notified in order to either seek a protective order or waive this agreement <br/>according to the disclosing party&#8217;s discretion. <br/> <br/>F: This agreement shall be governed under the jurisdiction of the state of: [State name] <br/> <br/> <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/> <br/> <br/>The undersigned agree to the terms of this agreement. <br/></p>
<p> (Name of Company)    (Name of Company) <br/>Name of Signatory:   Name of Signatory:  <br/>Date:   Date:  <br/> <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>

===== Non-Disclosure-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT  <br/></b></p>
<p><b>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Non-Disclosure Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into <br/>on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between ________________________, <br/>with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Disclosing Party&#8221;</b>) and <br/>________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <br/><b>&#8220;Receiving Party&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Receiving Party agrees not to disclose, copy, clone, or modify any confidential <br/>information related to the Disclosing Party and agrees not to use any such information without <br/>obtaining consent.  <br/></p>
<p>- &#8220;Confidential information&#8221; refers to any data and/or information that is related to the <br/>Disclosing Party, in any form, including, but not limited to, oral or written. Such confidential <br/>information includes, but is not limited to, any information related to the business or industry <br/>of the Disclosing Party, such as discoveries, processes, techniques, programs, knowledge <br/>bases, customer lists, potential customers, business partners, affiliated partners, leads, know-<br/>how, or any other services related to the Disclosing Party. <br/></p>
<p><b>RETURN OF CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Receiving Party agrees to return all the confidential information to the Disclosing Party <br/>upon the termination of this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p><b>OWNERSHIP <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is not transferable and may only be transferred by written consent provided <br/>by both Parties.  <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>DISCLOSING PARTY <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>RECEIVING PARTY <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>

<p>- Intellectual Property includes, but is not limited to, trademarks, trade names, service marks,<br/>service mark registrations, service names, patents, patent rights, copyrights, inventions,<br/>licenses, approvals, governmental authorizations, trade secrets, algorithms, codes,<br/>inventions, processes, software, formulas, ideas, concepts, and developments.<br/></p>

<p><b>- </b>Any dispute and/or difference arising out of or related to this Agreement will be submitted to<br/>________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) according to, and subject to the laws<br/>of ________________.<br/></p>

<p><b>- </b>This Agreement will be governed by and construed according to the laws of<br/>________________.<br/><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is complete and with respect to the subject matter herein, supersedes all and<br/>any prior agreements, understandings, and conditions, expressed or implied, written or oral,<br/>of any nature with respect to the subject matter herein.<br/></p>
<p>- The expressed terms control and supersede any course of performance and/or usage of the<br/>trade inconsistent with any of the terms herein.<br/></p>

===== Partnership-Business-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>[Company name] Partnership Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This partnership agreement is hereby entered into on this date: [Date here] <br/></p>
<p><b>Partners <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/></p>
<p>The Partners in this Agreement hereby agree to the following terms: <br/>Name: [Company name] <br/></p>
<p><b>Partnership <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The partners will become legal partners in [Company name]. <br/>2. This agreement will define the terms of the partnership. <br/>3. The partnership will come into effect on this date: [Date here] <br/>4. The partnership can only be terminated under the terms of this agreement. <br/>5. The partnership will conduct business in this primary place: [Place and location] <br/>6. The partnership will be governed by the state laws of: [State name] <br/>7. The primary purpose of the partnership is: [Purpose of the partnership] <br/></p>
<p><b>Contributions: <br/></b></p>
<p>This will be the initial contribution of the partners to the [Company name] partnership: <br/> <br/> <br/>The partners must submit contributions to a joint capital account by this date: [Date here] <br/> <br/>All contributions are final. <br/></p>
<p><b>Interest and Authority: <br/></b></p>
<p>The ownership interest of the partners is as follows: <br/> <br/>The authority of the partners in this partnership will be as follows: <br/></p>
<p><b>Costs: <br/></b></p>
<p>The partnership is responsible for cost sharing. The percentages of cost responsibility will be as follows: <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>Profits: <br/></b></p>
<p>The net profits of [Company name] will be divided as follows: <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>Salary:  </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>All partners must unanimously agree on the terms of a salary.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Accounting:  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. All accounts related to the partnership will be subject to auditing.  <br/>2. Joint contribution and distribution accounts will be maintained by partners.  <br/>3. Complete, accurate records shall be kept for all partnership accounts. These records may be viewed by <br/></p>
<p>any partner, at any time.  <br/>4. The authority to sign checks from partnership accounts is granted to the following partners: <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>New Partners:  <br/></b></p>
<p>This will be the [Company name] policy on accepting new partners:  <br/>1. This agreement will be amended on the unanimous vote of existing partners to include any new partners.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Withdrawal &amp; Dissolution:  <br/></b></p>
<p>This will be the [Company name] policy on withdrawing from the partnership:  <br/>1. The partners hereby reserve the right to withdraw from the partnership.  <br/>2. Upon a withdrawal by choice or by death, the remaining partners will have the option of purchasing <br/></p>
<p>remaining shares in the partnership. <br/>3. Dissolution of the partnership is by vote. Remaining funds after paying debt will be divided according to <br/></p>
<p>ownership percentages outlined above.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Dispute Resolution:  <br/></b></p>
<p>This will be the [Company name] policy on disputes among the partners: <br/> <br/>1. All partners agree to at least one session of mediation prior to filing a lawsuit against another partner. <br/>Lawsuits will be under the jurisdiction of this state: [State name] <br/> <br/></p>
<p>Signed <br/></p>
<p>Partner A:  Date:  <br/></p>
<p>Partner B:  Date:  <br/></p>
<p>Partner C:  Date:  <br/></p>
<p>Partner D:  Date:  <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>

===== Patent-License-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Patent License Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This agreement is hereby entered into on this date [Date here] between [Licensor&#8217;s name] . <br/></p>
<p>and [Licensee name] for the purpose of transferring the ownership of Patent # [patent number] from the <br/>licensor to the licensee. <br/> <br/><b>[Licensee name] <br/></b>[Address line 1 <br/>Address line 2 <br/>Address line 3] <br/>Tel: [Telephone number] <br/></p>
<p> <b>[Licensor&#8217;s name] <br/></b>[Address line 1 <br/>Address line 2 <br/>Address line 3]   <br/>Tel: [Telephone number] <br/></p>
<p> <br/>The licensor and licensee agree to the following terms: <br/></p>
<p><b>General Terms <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The licensor will transfer the ownership and rights of the patent license to the licensee.  <br/>2. The licensor has the authority to transfer the ownership and rights of the patent license to the licensee.  <br/>3. The licensee accepts the patent license and has the ability to pay the determined fees.  <br/>4. The licensor guarantees that the patent is licensed and valid.  <br/>5. This agreement is governed under the jurisdiction of the state of [State name] <br/></p>
<p><b>License Grant  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The licensor grants the patent license to the licensee subject to the licensee's performance of all payment <br/>obligations.  <br/></p>
<p>2. The licensee shall be entitled to the whole ownership of the patent and may subcontract manufacturing of <br/>licensed products under the patent to third parties.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Payments  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The licensee shall purchase the patent from the licensor at a sum of $15,000 in a single installment at the <br/>time of signing this agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>2. The payment shall be made to the licensor via bank transfer.  <br/>3. The amount paid to the licensor shall in no way be refunded or canceled.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Liability  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. Neither party shall be held liable for any damages, indirect or direct, including loss of profits or any <br/>commercial loss.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Publicity  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. This agreement is not strictly confidential.  <br/>2. Neither party shall disclose the contents of this agreement to a third party without prior consent with the <br/></p>
<p>exception of court-ordered disclosure or where otherwise required by the law.  <br/>3. In the event of a court-ordered disclosure of any or all portions of this agreement, the disclosing party must <br/></p>
<p>immediately alert the other party of the order.  <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/> <br/> <br/>The undersigned have hereby read all of this agreement and agree to abide by the terms and conditions <br/>therein. <br/> <br/></p>
<p>[Licensee name]  [Licenser&#8217;s name] <br/></p>
<p> [representative]    <br/></p>
<p>Date:   Date:  <br/> <br/> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>

<p>- The Parties agree that the Debtor is to pay the Creditor an amount of ________________ <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree to secure the amount of debt by entering into a new agreement where the <br/>amount of ________________ mentioned above is to be set into a structured payment <br/>agreement according to the terms and conditions provided below.  <br/></p>
<p><b>DEBTOR REPRESENTATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Debtor warrants as well as represents that the Parties have agreed upon a payment plan <br/>to secure the deficiency in a scheduled manner as set forth in this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENT PLAN <br/></b></p>

<p>- In case the Debtor fails to provide the payments as per the payment plans within a reasonable <br/>time, the Creditor becomes entitled to declare the remaining amount and the present Interest, <br/>if any, immediately due and payable.  <br/></p>

<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>

<p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. </p>

<p>- This Agreement contains the entire Agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>

<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>

===== Product-Distribution-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Product Distribution Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p> <br/>This agreement is hereby entered into on this date: [Date here] <br/>Between [ABC Toy Company], [Address] and [Best Department Stores, Inc.], [Address]. <br/> <br/><b>Purpose:</b> To grant [Best Department Stores, Inc.] (hereinafter referred to as &#8220;The Distributor&#8221;) the rights to <br/>distribute for sale the [A0001] product line (hereinafter referred to as &#8220;The Product&#8221;) manufactured by [ABC Toy <br/>Company] (hereinafter referred to as &#8220;The Manufacturer&#8221;).  <br/> <br/>Both parties hereby agree to the following terms and conditions:  <br/></p>
<p><b>Rights  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The Manufacturer exclusively owns the product.  <br/>2. The Distributor is granted non-exclusive rights to sell the product in accordance with the terms of this <br/></p>
<p>agreement.  <br/>3. The Distributor will put forth its best efforts in achieving sales of The Product.  <br/>4. Terms and prices of The Product will be determined mutually by the parties.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Profits  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The Distributor will turn over a portion of the profits from sales of The Product in the amount of 75 percent.  <br/>2. The portion of profits turned over to The Manufacturer will follow a schedule mutually agreed upon by both <br/></p>
<p>parties.  <br/>3. Along with each payment, The Distributor will submit a written report to The Manufacturer.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Records  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. Accurate and complete records will be kept by The Distributor in regards to sales of The Product.  <br/>2. The Manufacturer may review these records at any time.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Title to Merchandise  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The Product will remain legal property of The Manufacturer until being sold.  <br/>2. The Distributor is responsible for loss, damage or shortage of merchandise under its control.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Taxes  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. The Distributor is responsible for employee payroll taxes.  <br/>2. The Manufacturer is indemnified against any liability regarding The Distributor&#8217;s employee payroll taxes.  <br/></p>
<p><b>Defaults  <br/></b></p>
<p>1. In the event of any failure of The Distributor to abide by the terms of this agreement, including but not <br/>limited to remittance of payments due, The Manufacturer will have the option to terminate this agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>2. The Distributor may terminate this agreement in the event of a breach committed by The Manufacturer.  <br/>3. Either party must provide a written notice of 45 days in the event of termination. <br/> <br/>The undersigned hereby agree to the above terms and conditions. <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>[ABC Toy Company] </b> <b>[Best Department Stores, Inc.]</b> <br/>Name of Signatory:   Name of Signatory:  <br/>Date:   Date:  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>

You can (and should!) remove this copyright notice (click here to see how) before customizing <br/>the template. <br/>  <br/>You may not distribute or resell this template, or its derivatives, and you may not make it available on other websites <br/>without our prior permission. <div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Professional Service Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p>The following [AGREEMENT] is drafted on this the [_____] day of the month of [______________], in the year <br/>[________]. [THEATER INC.], located at [THEATER INC. ADDRESS], henceforth known as The Company, <br/>and [JOHN SMITH CONTRACTORS], located at [JOHN SMITH CONTRACTORS&#8216; ADDRESS], henceforth <br/>known as The Contractor, agree to the following conditions of service: <br/></p>
<p>The Contractor is to perform all tasks on site. The site, located at [SITE&#8217;S ADDRESS], in the State of [STATE <br/>NAME] shall remain accessible to The Contractor during the hours of [__:___ AM/PM] until [__:___ AM/PM], <br/>during the entire duration of the agreement between The Contractor and The Company. The starting date of <br/>this agreement is [STARTING DATE]. The ending date of this agreement is [ENDING DATE]. <br/></p>
<p>The Company expects the following from The Contractor: The building of the predesigned set, the painting of <br/>the predesigned set, and the building of the one chair, one bar, and one table. All of the required projects have <br/>been designed and articulated by the [THEATER INC.] set designer. The Contractor shall meet all of the <br/>required measurements and particulars of this project as in the design provided. The Contractor will provide <br/>The Company with a list of materials needed to perform the services requested. The Company holds the rights <br/>to all of the designs. The Contractor is not allowed to show the designs to an outside source, nor sell the <br/>designs, nor take the designs off of the premises. <br/></p>
<p>The Company shall pay The Contractor the amount of $[AMOUNT] by the date of [DATE]. The Company shall <br/>pay The Contractor the amount of $[AMOUNT] by the completion of the services requested. The payment shall <br/>be made in two installations. The payment shall be made to [JOHN SMITH CONTRACTORS], to the bank of <br/>[BANK NAME], located at [BANK ADDRESS] to the account number [ACCOUNT NUMBER] with the routing <br/>number of [ROUTING NUMBER]. <br/></p>
<p>The Company holds all rights to refuse final payment if the services are found to be unsatisfactory, dangerous, <br/>or not to the specifications of the designs provided. The Contractor has the right to seek payment by any <br/>means necessary if the work was satisfactory, and the final payment is not made by the above-mentioned <br/>date. <br/></p>
<p>The undersigned agree to all of the conditions above: <br/></p>
<p><b>[THEATER INC.]: <br/></b></p>
<p>Representative Name:  <br/></p>
<p>Address:  <br/></p>
<p>Telephone:  Email:  <br/></p>
<p>Representative Signature:  Date:  <br/> <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>
<p><b>[JOHN SMITH CONTRACTORS]: <br/></b></p>
<p>Representative Name:  <br/></p>
<p>Address:  <br/></p>
<p>Telephone:  Email:  <br/></p>
<p>Representative Signature:  Date:  <br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>[WITNESS]: <br/></b></p>
<p>Witness Name:  <br/></p>

===== Profit-Sharing-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title>PROFIT SHARING AGREEMENT.docx</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>PROFIT SHARING CONTRACTUAL AGREEMENT<br/>PARTIES<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Investment Contractual Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is<br/>entered into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between<br/>________________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred<br/>to as the <b>&#8220;Company&#8221;</b>) and ________________with an address of ________________<br/>(hereinafter r referred to as the <b>&#8220;Representative&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the<br/><b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>).<br/></p>
<p><b>TERM<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is valid from the day of its signing until ________________.<br/><b>PROFIT SHARING<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that the Representative is entitled to ________________ % of the<br/>product profits. This is based on the direct result of the Representative&#8217;s efforts.<br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that a &#8220;direct result&#8221; is defined as any contact made with a customer that<br/>led to a sale.<br/></p>
<p>- The Parties further agree that profits are calculated as follows<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/></p>
<p><b>RESPONSIBILITIES<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Representative is entitled to perform the research and any other<br/>duties required regarding potential customers, to compete paperwork (if any), and to<br/>perform any other tasks that may or may not be assigned by the Company.<br/></p>
<p><b>RELATIONSHIP OF THE PARTIES<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the relationship between them will be as independent contractors.<br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY<br/></b></p>
<p>- During the Term and for a period of ________________ years thereafter, the<br/>Representative agrees to maintain in confidence all the Company&#8217;s information disclosed<br/>that is identified as, or acknowledged to be, confidential at the time of disclosure (the<br/>&#8220;Confidential Information&#8221;), and shall not use, disclose or grant the use of the<br/>Confidential Information.</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>EFFECT OF TERMINATION<br/></b></p>
<p>Upon termination, the Parties agree on the following:<br/></p>
<p>- The Representative will continue to receive his/her profit share resulting from the<br/>continuation of sales directing resulting from his/her effort.<br/></p>
<p>- The Representative will be obliged to direct to the Company any inquiries or questions<br/>related to the product.<br/></p>
<p>- The Representative will destroy/return any information that belongs to the Company<br/>that is in his/her possession.<br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS<br/></b>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing where<br/></p>
<p>they must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.<br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement.<br/><b>SEVERABILITY<br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where a provision of this Agreement is found to be void and/or unenforceable by<br/>a court of competent jurisdiction, then the provisions remaining will continue to be enforced.<br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION<br/></b></p>
<p><b>- </b>Any dispute and/or difference arising out of or related to this Agreement will be submitted to<br/>________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) according to, and subject to the laws<br/>of ________________.<br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW<br/></b></p>
<p><b>- </b>This Agreement will be governed by and construed according to the laws of<br/>________________.<br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT<br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is complete and with respect to the subject matter herein, supersedes all and<br/>any prior agreements, understandings, and conditions, expressed or implied, written or oral,<br/>of any nature with respect to the subject matter herein.<br/></p>
<p>- The expressed terms control and supersede any course of performance and/or usage of the<br/>trade inconsistent with any of the terms herein.</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE<br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is<br/>demonstrated throughout their signatures below:<br/></p>
<p>COMPANY<br/></p>
<p>_______________________________<br/></p>
<p>REPRESENTATIVE<br/></p>
<p>_______________________________<br/></p>
<p>DATE<br/></p>
<p>_______________________________<br/></p>
<p>DATE<br/></p>
<p>_______________________________</p>

===== Property-Management-Agreement-Template-Signaturely.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>PROPERTY MANAGEMENT <br/>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p><b>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Property Management Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered <br/>into on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between <br/>________________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred to <br/>as the <b>&#8220;Owner&#8221;</b>), and ________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter <br/>referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agent&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>GENERAL <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Owner exclusively appoints the Agent to manage the property that is located at <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p>- The Agent hereby accepts such responsibility and agrees to manage the property <br/>aforementioned.  <br/>The Owner agrees to pay the fees associated with the services that the Agent will provide <br/>when managing the aforementioned property.  <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on _______________________________.  <br/></p>
<p><b>THE RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE AGENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- To rent and lease as well as operate the property. <br/></p>
<p>- To collect rent and monies applicable from potential tenants in due time. However, the Agent <br/>will not bear the responsibilities of the potential tenants in case of refusal of payment or <br/>other. <br/></p>
<p>- To provide a monthly accounting of rents received and paid expenses as well as any other <br/>applicable incomes, monies or sums to the Owner.  <br/></p>
<p>- To decorate, improve, repair and maintain the property when needed. <br/></p>
<p>- To hire as well as supervise employees (if any) when needed.  <br/></p>
<p>- To inform the Owner of any improvements and repairs that exceed _________________ and <br/>to obtain consent from the Owner prior to paying such fees. <br/></p>
<p><b>AGENT LIABILITY </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- Hereby, the Owner agrees to hold the Agent harmless from any debts, charges, demands, <br/>claims and/or lawsuits.  <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENT AND FEES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the total cost of the services will be ____________, <br/></p>
<p>where ____________ will be paid at the signing of this Agreement and ____________ will <br/>be paid at completion. <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Agent will provide an invoice to the Owner every ____________ <br/>days/months for the Services he/she completes. <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the means of payment will be via <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in case the following occurs: <br/>Immediately in case one of the Parties breaches this Agreement or one of the conditions set <br/>forth in this Agreement and does not amend the issue within a period of ________________. <br/>This Agreement will automatically be terminated in case the premises is not rented in a <br/>period of ________________ from the date of signing this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SUCCESSION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement is binding on the Agent and the Owner as well as their successors. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW</b> <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing and they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree not to assign any of the responsibilities in this Agreement to a third <br/>party unless consented by both Parties in writing.  <br/></p>
<p><b>ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p><b> </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to ________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) (Circle one) in <br/>accordance with, and subject to the laws of, ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated throughout by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>OWNER <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>AGENT <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>

===== Real-Estate-Partnership-Agreement.html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Real Estate Partnership Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p>[Partner #1 Name], residing at [Partner #1 Address], and [Partner #2 Name], residing at [Partner #2 Address], <br/>henceforth referred to as the &#8220;Partners&#8221;, hereby agree to all of the terms and conditions set forth in the <br/>following [PARTNERSHIP AGREEMENT]: <br/></p>
<p>The Partners agree to the purchase of the properties located at [Property #1 location], [Property #2 location], <br/>[Property #3 location], and [Property #4 location], in the City of [City Name], in the State of [State Name]. <br/></p>
<p>The Partners agree to pay the amount of $ [Amount] for the property located at [Property #1 location]. The <br/>Partners agree to pay the amount of $ [Amount] for the property located at [Property #2 location]. The Partners <br/>agree to pay the amount of $ [Amount] for the property located at [Property #3 location]. The Partners agree to <br/>pay the amount of $ [Amount] for the property located at [Property #4 location]. The Partners agree to pay <br/>these amounts to the bank [Bank Name] located at [Bank address], by the [_____] day in the month of <br/>[_______________] in the year [_______]. <br/></p>
<p>The Partners agree to pay the amount of $ [Amount] towards renovations of each of the above-mentioned <br/>properties. <br/></p>
<p>The Partners shall both enter into this agreement on equal terms. No one Partner may make any decisions <br/>concerning the above-mentioned properties without the express consent of the other Partner. Both Partners <br/>agree to hire [Property managing company name] as the property managing company for all of the above-<br/>mentioned properties. The Partners agree that all maintenance contractors, plumbers, decorators, and <br/>electricians hired for the above-mentioned properties shall be agreed upon at a later date. <br/></p>
<p>The responsibilities of both Partners are as follows: Equal amounts are to be paid by both Partners concerning <br/>maintenance of the properties. Equal amounts are to be paid by both Partners concerning property taxes. <br/>Equal amounts are to be paid by both Partners concerning mortgage. Both Partners are to keep detailed <br/>records of payments made in all matters concerning the properties. Both Partners are to maintain contact with <br/>the above mentioned property Management Company every [______] months concerning the care of the <br/>properties. <br/></p>
<p>In the event that one of the Partners wishes to dissolve their shares of the above-mentioned properties, the <br/>Partners have agreed that the properties are to be sold and the money shared equally between the Partners.  <br/></p>
<p>I, [Partner #1 Name], on this the [_____] day of the month of [________________], in the year [_____], hereby <br/>agree to all of the terms and conditions laid out in this agreement. <br/></p>
<p>Partner Signature: ______________________________________  <br/></p>
<p>I, [Partner #2 Name], on this the [_____] day of the month of [________________], in the year [_____], hereby <br/>agree to all of the terms and conditions laid out in this agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>Partner Signature: ______________________________________  <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>     <br/>Witness Name  Witness Signature  Date </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>
<p>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p> <br/></p>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"

<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>REFERRAL AGREEMENT <br/>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Referral Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into on <br/>________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between ________________________, <br/>with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Referrer&#8221;</b>), and <br/>________________, with an address of ________________ (hereinafter referred to as the <br/><b>&#8220;Seller&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p>- The Seller is in the business of ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- The Referrer has contacts with __________________ and has agreed to act as an intermediary <br/>finder of clients for the Seller and his/her services.  <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be automatically <br/>renewed for a new term. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in case the following occurs: <br/>Immediately in case one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- At any given time by providing a written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN PARTIES  <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties agree that the Referrer in this Agreement is an independent contractor <br/>where the Referrer provides the services hereunder and acts as an independent contractor. <b> <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances shall the Referrer be considered an employee. <b> <br/></b></p>
<p>- Whereas, this Agreement does not create any other partnership between the Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENT AND FEES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Referrer will receive ________________ commission per referral. <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Referrer will provide an invoice to the Seller every ____________ <br/>days/months for the Services he/she completes. <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- The Parties agree that the means of payment will be via <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- All terms and conditions of this Agreement and any materials provided during the term of the <br/>Agreement must be kept confidential by the Referrer, unless the disclosure is required pursuant <br/>to the process of law.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Referrer will not be entitled to use any information provided to him/her even after the <br/>conclusion of the Agreement for a period of ________________ years.  <br/></p>
<p>- Disclosing or using this information for any purpose beyond the scope of this Agreement, or <br/>beyond the exceptions set forth above, is expressly forbidden without the prior consent of the <br/>Seller. <br/></p>
<p>- This section will remain in force regardless of the fact in case the Agreement is terminated. <br/></p>
<p>- The Referrer is not to use the Seller&#8217;s information for advertisements or any other <br/>promotional activity without the Seller&#8217;s written consent.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Referrer is not to use any intellectual property provided to him/her by the Seller without <br/>the written consent of the Seller.  <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of or relating to this Agreement or the <br/>transactions it contemplates (whether for breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action) in case such is not related to the direct result of one party&#8217;s negligence or breach. <br/></p>
<p><b>INDEMNITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree not to indemnify and hold one another harmless. This also applies to their <br/>affiliates, agents, officers, employees, and/or successors. The Parties in this Agreement hereby <br/>in addition agree to assign against all (if any) claims, liabilities, damages, losses, penalties, <br/>punitive damages, expenses, any reasonable legal fees and/or costs of any kind or any amount <br/>that may arise. This includes, but is not limited to, any amount which may result from the <br/>negligence of or the breach of this Agreement by the party that is indemnified, its successors <br/>and assigns that occurs in terms of this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- This section will remain in full force and tact as well as effect even upon the termination of the <br/>Agreement naturally or the early termination by either of the Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be <br/>submitted to ________________ (Arbitration/mediation/negotiation) in accordance with, and <br/>subject to the laws of, ________________.  <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________.<b> <br/></b></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In an event where any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain to be enforced in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire Agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>

<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>

<p><b>TERMS <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be automatically renewed <br/>for a new term. <br/></p>

<p>- The Parties agree that in the event that the invoices are not paid within thirty days of receipt, <br/>the Contractor will be entitled to charge a late fee of ________________. <br/></p>

<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- Accordingly, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree not to assign any of the responsibilities in this Agreement to a third <br/>party, unless consented by both Parties in writing.  <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT </b></p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof. <br/></p>
<p><b>REPRESENTATION AND WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree and disclose that they are fully authorized to enter this Agreement. The <br/>performances and obligations of both Parties are not to violate the rights of any third party or <br/>else violate other, if any, agreements made between them and/or any other organization, <br/>person, business or law/governmental regulation.  <br/></p>
<p><b>DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Contractor warrants to complete the Services listed in this Agreement as per the Client&#8217;s <br/>requirements and specifications. However, the Contractor does not represent or warrant that <br/>such services provided in this Agreement will create additional sales, exposure, brand <br/>recognition, profits or other similar benefits.  <br/></p>
<p>- In addition to the above, the Contractor holds no responsibility towards the Client in the event <br/>that the delivered work doesn&#8217;t lead to the Client&#8217;s desired results.  <br/></p>
<p><b>LIMITATION OF LIABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances will either Party be liable for any indirect, special, consequential, or <br/>punitive damages (including lost profits) arising out of or relating to this Agreement or the <br/>transactions it contemplates (whether for breach of contract, tort, negligence, or other form of <br/>action) in the event that such is not related to the direct result of one of the Parties&#8217; negligence <br/>or breach. <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>

<p>- Under no circumstances shall the Consultant be considered an employee, representative, agent <br/>or partner.  <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement does not create any other partnership between the Parties. <br/></p>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>- The Parties agree that this is a non-exclusive agreement and that the Parties are regarded as <br/>independent contractors.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- Accordingly, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties are not entitled to assign the responsibilities that they have under this Agreement <br/>to anyone else, unless both Parties agree to the assignment and provide such agreement in <br/>writing. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties to it with <br/>respect to its subject matter, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, inducements <br/>and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with respect to its <br/>subject matter. The express terms of the Agreement control and supersede any course of <br/>performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of its terms.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of, or in connection with, this Agreement <br/>shall be submitted to arbitration/mediation/negotiation (circle one) in accordance with, and <br/>subject to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
