===== Signaturely-SEO-Proposal-Template (1).html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Introduction <br/>Your company needs to have a strong digital presence in this digital world. The best way to <br/>achieve online success is by having a solid SEO strategy. <br/> <br/>SEO can help you increase your organic traffic and get highly-qualified users to discover your <br/>website and learn about what you have to offer. With a good SEO strategy, your website can <br/>reach far more viewers for much longer than any ads of the same price could. <br/> <br/>According to our research, the implementation of a good SEO strategy can help you increase <br/>organic page views and visits by up to 20% in just six months and even more with additional <br/>strategies. <br/> <br/>If you have any questions or comments about this proposal, please don&#8217;t hesitate to contact me <br/>by responding to the email this proposal was attached to. <br/></p>
<p>About Us <br/>The Ranking Consultant Agency is a company dedicated to helping startups reach their targeted <br/>audience and increase their online visibility. <br/> <br/>Started in 2012 by three friends, The Ranking Consultant Agency has grown to employ over 25 <br/>people on-site and across the world, which enables us to employ the best talent at competitive <br/>prices. <br/> <br/>At The Ranking Consultant Agency, we assist start-ups through data-based decisions, starting <br/>with thorough research, establishing goals, and letting you know how much you can increase <br/>your visibility and how to increase and maintain your level of traffic. <br/> <br/>Our company has helped over 100 brands increase their traffic exclusively through SEO, and <br/>we&#8217;re ready to do the same for you. <br/></p>
<p>Our Approach <br/>At The Ranking Consultant Agency, we start our process by establishing where your company <br/>is at. This means looking into how your company is doing on SEO, like the amount of organic <br/>traffic you&#8217;re already getting, which keywords your website is currently ranking for, and which <br/>are your most important keywords overall. <br/> <br/>We&#8217;ll also verify if there are any potential issues with your website that&#8217;s keeping you from <br/>ranking, and how to solve them. This will help us establish a baseline. <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Establishing a baseline is extremely important because it lets us know where we are, and allows <br/>us to create realistic and achievable goals.  <br/> <br/>It also helps us discover any potential issues that might be preventing your company from <br/>achieving its goals. We can then solve these in order to start on a solid foundation. <br/> <br/>Once we establish your baseline and your needs we will start developing your SEO strategy and <br/>supervise it to fruition. <br/> <br/>Here&#8217;s what our auditing process looks like: <br/></p>
<p>1. Laying the groundwork <br/>We begin the process by using various tools to crawl your website. These tools let us collect the <br/>information we need to learn how well your website is currently ranking. <br/> <br/>We also check your analytics to discover trends and patterns about your traffic and use the free <br/>Google Webmasters diagnostic tools. <br/> <br/>Once we have collected all the data we need, we start the audit process. <br/></p>
<p>2. Discovering your website&#8217;s accessibility <br/>By using the data we&#8217;ve collected, we will learn how well search engines are currently able to <br/>crawl and access your website. We look for potential issues in your website&#8217;s metadata, <br/>sitemaps, site architecture, navigation, and framework. <br/> <br/>This lets us know two things: how well search engines can access your website and how well <br/>search engines can understand your website. <br/> <br/>Finally, we check your site&#8217;s performance&#8212;how fast it loads on a computer or smartphone. <br/></p>
<p>3. Finding out your indexability <br/>Once we make sure search engines can access and understand your website, we need to make <br/>sure they can index it too. <br/> <br/>&#8220;Indexing&#8221; means search engines are including your website in their results when someone <br/>looks up relevant information. <br/> <br/>This part is very simple to do. We search various queries on Google and Bing and find out how <br/>many of the pages from your website are included in the results. <br/> <br/>If any pages can&#8217;t be accessed, we&#8217;ll offer solutions to help you index them. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>4. On-page optimization <br/>Once we&#8217;ve ensured your website is indexed and SEO-friendly, we dig into the rest of the <br/>factors that determine your ranking. <br/> <br/>We consider factors such as: <br/></p>
<p>&#9679; URLs <br/>&#9679; Content <br/>&#9679; Duplicate Content <br/>&#9679; Keyword Cannibalism <br/>&#9679; HTML markup <br/>&#9679; Interlinking <br/></p>
<p>These factors will help us find even more ways to improve your ranking. <br/></p>
<p>5. Off-page optimization <br/>When it comes to ranking, what&#8217;s not on your website is just as important as what is on it. Your <br/>website needs to have high-quality sites linking to it. These links, or backlinks, help determine <br/>your page authority. <br/> <br/>Here, we review your website&#8217;s popularity compared to your competition, your backlinks and <br/>their sources, how trustworthy your website is, as well as your Page Authority and Domain <br/>Authority. Based on this analysis, we take action and start building links to your site through <br/>different tactics. <br/></p>
<p>6. Competition analysis <br/>Once we&#8217;ve reviewed everything there is to review about your website, we&#8217;ll also review three of <br/>your competitors&#8217; websites and compare the results. <br/> <br/>Finally, we determine the actions that need to be taken to increase your website&#8217;s ranking. <br/></p>
<p>Issues <br/>In reviewing your website, we&#8217;ll learn about any issues it may have. These can include the <br/>following: <br/></p>
<p>Missing Alt Tags and Broken Images <br/>Images must always be fully responsive since broken images are bad for SEO. However, since <br/>Google can&#8217;t see the images, it relies on alt tags to know what the image represents.  <br/> <br/>Alt tags help search engines understand what images are about and their relevance to the <br/>content. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Meta Descriptions Issues <br/>Meta descriptions help users decide whether they should click on your website when they find it <br/>on a search engine. If your meta descriptions aren&#8217;t attractive enough, users may look <br/>elsewhere. The fewer clicks your website gets, the lower the search engine will rank it. <br/> <br/>By providing relevant meta descriptions, you ensure users will click on your website and help <br/>your website rank higher. <br/></p>
<p>Low Word Count <br/>When it comes to SEO, there's no minimum word count; however, words help search engines <br/>understand the purpose of a page. <br/> <br/>And it&#8217;s not just about how many words are written either. Google in particular seems to prefer <br/>deep and valuable content, rather than fluff. <br/> <br/>Your content should be as long as it needs to be to convey the right information, without any <br/>unnecessary repetition or rephrasing. <br/></p>
<p>Broken Internal and External Links <br/>Having broken links can be extremely damaging for your SEO. While a couple of broken links <br/>are usually not a big problem, the more your website contains, the less friendly it will appear to <br/>both users and search engines. <br/> <br/>This is especially true of search engines because they don&#8217;t typically crawl your whole website <br/>at one time. So the more broken links you have, the more likely it is that a search engine won&#8217;t <br/>find the content it is looking for. <br/></p>
<p>Objectives &amp; Solutions <br/>Based on the issues above, we can decide which path to take to fix any problems and help your <br/>website rank even higher. <br/> <br/>Here are the proposed objectives and solutions for your website: <br/></p>
<p>Improve meta descriptions <br/>We need to ensure all pages have a proper meta description that&#8217;s both informative and <br/>relevant to the rest of the page. <br/> <br/>To achieve this, we need to keep meta descriptions at a limit of 155 characters to ensure as <br/>much information is conveyed without anything getting cropped out. <br/> </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>We should also improve meta descriptions to make them sound actionable by making sure they <br/>all have a proper CTA. Finally, we need to ensure the meta descriptions include the most <br/>important keyword, all while matching the rest of the content. <br/></p>
<p>Fix image issues <br/>Next, we need to ensure your website&#8217;s images have the proper tags and are fully functional. <br/> <br/>All alt tags should describe images using less than 125 characters. They should also use <br/>relevant keywords when possible. <br/></p>
<p>Increase word count <br/>Not all pages need to contain a lot of content. However, we need to ensure all pages have <br/>enough content to fully inform users and search engines of their purpose. <br/> <br/>To achieve this, we need to find pages with content issues and improve the text in them without <br/>using any unnecessary words. The text should be easy to read, easy to scan, and to the point. <br/></p>
<p>Fix broken links <br/>We need to find every broken link. These broken links will be tracked on a spreadsheet.  <br/> <br/>We will then find the relevant active links to replace each of the broken links, which will also help <br/>with interlinking. <br/></p>
<p>Create an SEO campaign <br/>The final and most important step of this process is the creation of an SEO campaign. Our SEO <br/>team will build a framework so you can increase your rankings and organic traffic. This <br/>framework will increase new visitors and maintain regular visitors while giving you an edge over <br/>the competition. <br/></p>
<p>Past Projects &amp; Achievements <br/>Here&#8217;s how we&#8217;ve helped other users in the past: <br/></p>
<p>Case Study: Local Photographer <br/>Jennifer Doe had had her photography studio for over three years, and in spite of her business <br/>being successful, she was struggling to obtain online traffic. Although her website was running, <br/>barely any users were visiting it. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Proposed Solution <br/>We started by identifying the types of clients she wanted to target. Although many people visited <br/>her studio, she wanted to target more weddings and enable clients to find her online and have <br/>her shoot on location. <br/> <br/>We audited her website, which had few but important issues. Once her website had been <br/>audited and fully optimized, we started performing competition research to find out which <br/>keywords users were using in their searches. <br/> <br/>When we got the right keywords, we developed a plan to help users find her more easily: We <br/>optimized the content she already had with the right keywords, and we developed more content <br/>to target those keywords. <br/> <br/>We rewrote 75% of her website content, so the content would be far more friendly and targeted. <br/>We then created a blog to target even more long-tail keywords and allow her to display more <br/>about her work and process. <br/></p>
<p>Result <br/>Within the first month, she had already received 4 highly-qualified leads that ended up <br/>converting and purchasing wedding packages. By the end of the six months, she had received <br/>55 queries from highly-qualified users who had found her page organically. <br/> <br/>&#8220;I started without knowing anything about SEO. The Ranking Consulting Agency not only fixed <br/>everything that needed fixing but gave me the tools to keep up my website&#8217;s success.&#8221; <br/>Jeniffer Doe, professional photographer. <br/></p>
<p>Pricing &amp; ROI <br/>Our pricing will depend on the amount of work your website needs and the goals you&#8217;re aiming <br/>for. <br/> <br/><b>SEO audit</b>: We&#8217;ll audit your website to see how well it is doing with all major search engines. <br/>We will then identify any issues, and help you fix them. <br/><b>Price</b>: $XXX <br/> <br/><b>SEO Campaign Development</b>: We&#8217;ll audit your website and fix any issues it may have. We will <br/>then use the knowledge gained from the audit to develop a sustainable campaign to further <br/>increase your organic traffic. <br/><b>Price</b>: $XXX <br/> <br/><b>SEO Campaign Launch</b>: We&#8217;ll audit your website and fix any SEO issues it may have. We will <br/>then develop a campaign and carry it on to fruition over six months. Once those six months </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>have ended, we&#8217;ll repeat the process by completing another audit and developing another SEO <br/>campaign. <br/><b>Price</b>: $XXX <br/></p>
<p>Project Timeline <br/>If your company chooses The Ranking Consultant Agency to increase its organic traffic and <br/>develop an SEO campaign, the timeline will go as follows: <br/></p>
<p>Initial Interview <br/>During our initial interview, we talk with you to learn about any issues you&#8217;re encountering and <br/>what expectations you have from the process. <br/> <br/>This lets us start on solid ground since we can focus on the issues you want to have fixed. <br/><b> <br/>Time to completion</b>: A couple of hours. <br/></p>
<p>Phase One: Auditing <br/>Once we&#8217;ve had an initial meeting, The Ranking Consultant Agency will analyze your website&#8217;s <br/>issues and current performance.  <br/> <br/>We will give you all data collected from your website and provide you with the suggested actions <br/>to solve any issues. <br/> <br/><b>Time to completion</b>: Five business days. <br/></p>
<p>Phase Two: Immediate Website Improvement <br/>Once we&#8217;ve shown you the immediate issues we need to solve on your website and have a <br/>written agreement in place, our team will start fixing them. This will involve such things as fixing <br/>broken links, adding tags, and developing interlinking and content schedules. <br/> <br/><b>Time to completion</b>: Five business days. <br/></p>
<p>SEO Campaign Launch <br/>When your website is fully optimized, we&#8217;ll launch the SEO campaign.  <br/> <br/>This campaign usually includes content development, interlinking efforts, backlinking efforts, <br/>and any other long-term solutions to help you rank for the desired keywords. <br/> <br/><b>Time to completion</b>: Three to six months. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>SEO Campaign Management and Optimization <br/>Once the campaign is over, we&#8217;ll audit the results of the campaign and audit your website once <br/>more. We&#8217;ll also perform a second competitor&#8217;s audit for comparison. <br/> <br/>These audits will help us find more keywords and optimization opportunities. We will then <br/>translate those into actionable items for the next six months. <br/> <br/><b>Time to completion</b>: Six months. <br/></p>
<p>Why You Should Work With Us <br/>Your website doesn&#8217;t just need traffic, it needs qualified traffic. At The Ranking Consultant <br/>Agency, we understand that the best traffic is qualified traffic, and we optimize and develop all <br/>of our strategies with this in mind. <br/> <br/>Here&#8217;s how we ensure this: <br/></p>
<p>Bringing you traffic and helping it convert <br/>Since we&#8217;re looking for <i>qualified</i> traffic, our success measurements also measure conversion, <br/>not just traffic.  <br/> <br/>We keep you updated on progress, and we let you know what users will be expecting to help <br/>you guide them to conversion. <br/></p>
<p>Proven strategies for long-lasting SEO results <br/>At The Ranking Consultant Agency, we don&#8217;t just improve your results only to let them die when <br/>search engines change their algorithms.  <br/> <br/>By using a multi-channel SEO approach, we ensure that we are safely and permanently <br/>increasing your website traffic.  <br/></p>
<p>Giving you the attention you need <br/>We don&#8217;t accept every customer that shows up. Instead, we&#8217;re very careful about selecting our <br/>customers. We only select customers who have a lot of potential for measurable growth during <br/>the time of our audit and optimization processes. <br/> <br/>This not only allows us to focus on those with a higher chance of success, but it also lets us give <br/>you the best attention needed. You will not only see results but fully understand the strategies <br/>that led to them </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Terms of Agreement <br/>This SEO Proposal (&#8220;Proposal&#8221;) is being made between [Customer Name] located at [Address] <br/>and [Company Name] on [date]. [Customer Name] and [Company Name] may also be referred <br/>to as &#8220;Party&#8221; or together as the &#8220;Parties&#8221;. <br/> <br/></p>

<p>Intellectual Property <br/>[Customer Name] will own all content [Company Name] will design, including meta descriptions, <br/>alt tags, visuals, written content, and any graphic art developed for it. [Company Name] isn&#8217;t <br/>required to keep copies of the content or fragments of it. [Customer Name] will not hold <br/>[Company Name] responsible for any third-party claims. <br/> <br/>[Company name] will own any and all copyrightable work, ideas, products, inventions, and other <br/>information created in connection with the services being provided and will remain legal owners <br/>of them, not holding [customer name] responsible for any third-party claims. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>Confidentiality <br/>[Company Name] will not share or disclose any confidential information belonging to [Customer <br/>Name] without written consent. This may include but is not limited to trade secrets, payment <br/>information, and any other information not publicly available. <br/></p>
<p>Assignment <br/>The Parties will not assign responsibilities within this Agreement to anyone else unless both <br/>Parties show agreement to the assignment in writing. <br/></p>
<p>Contract Termination <br/>If [Customer Name] decides to terminate this contract, they may do so by providing a fifteen (15) <br/>day written notice and paying [Company Name] for all completed services. <br/> <br/>If either Party fails to follow through with their responsibilities or obligations under this <br/>Agreement, the other Party can end this Agreement by giving a five (5) day written notice. This <br/>Agreement will automatically terminate if and when both Parties have performed all of their <br/>obligations under the Agreement and all payments have been made. <br/></p>
<p>Acceptance <br/>Please sign below to indicate acceptance of this agreement: <br/> <br/>[Customer Name] <br/>Name: <br/>Signature: <br/>Date:   <br/> <br/>[Company Name]   <br/>Name: <br/>Signature: <br/>Date:   <br/></p>
<p>Next Steps <br/>If you want to start increasing your website&#8217;s traffic through SEO, here&#8217;s what you need to do: <br/></p>
<p>1. Review the proposal in its entirety. <br/>2. Sign the fields above. <br/>3. Wait for our emails with your invoice details and billing. </p>

</div></div>

<p>- Whereas, the Agent agrees not to pursue the selling of a competing product for any competitor <br/>during the term of this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that the Principal authorizes the Agent to sell <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>___________________________________________________________________________ <br/>on behalf of the Principal and the Agent agrees to indemnify himself/herself as the authorized <br/>agent of the Principal for such sale.  <br/></p>
<p><b>THE SALE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the prices of the product will be set by the Principal, that the Principal <br/>will obtain and provide the promotional materials (if any) for the Agent to use and to obtain <br/>sales, and the Principal will provide a Sales Agreement to the Agent for the Agent to use in the <br/>sale of the product.  <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;Effective Date&#8221;) and will end on ___________________________.  <br/></p>
<p>- The term of this Agreement may be extended upon the provision of written consent from both <br/>Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>GEOGRAPHY <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Agent will sell the product in the following geographical area/ <br/>territory _____________________________________________________ and will not sell <br/>the product anywhere else.  <br/></p>
<p><b>COMMISSION EARNINGS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree that the Agent will be paid by the Principal by the following means <br/>___________________________________________________________________________</p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>RELATIONSHIP OF THE PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties agree that this is a non-exclusive agreement and that the Parties are <br/>regarded as independent contractors.  <br/></p>
<p><b>CONFIDENTIALITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- All terms and conditions of this Agreement and any materials provided during the term of the <br/>Agreement must be kept confidential, unless the disclosure is required pursuant to process of <br/>law.  <br/></p>
<p>- Disclosing or using this information for any purpose beyond the scope of this Agreement, or <br/>beyond the exceptions set forth above, is expressly forbidden without the prior consent of the <br/>Client. <br/></p>
<p>- This section will remain in full force even after the termination of this Agreement for a period <br/>of __________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in the event that any of the following occurs: <br/></p>
<p>1. Immediately, in the event that one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>3. Upon terminating this Agreement, the Agent will be required to return all the Principal&#8217;s <br/>products and/or any other content (if any) at his/her earliest convenience, but not beyond <br/>________________ days. <br/></p>
<p><b>REPRESENTATION AND WARRANTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree and disclose that they are fully authorized to enter this Agreement. The <br/>performances and obligations of both Parties may not violate the rights of any third party or <br/>violate any other agreement made between them and/or any other organization, person, <br/>business or law/governmental regulation.  <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention.  <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW </b></p>

<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- As such, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>ASSIGNMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree not to assign any of the responsibilities in this Agreement to a third <br/>party, unless such is consented to by both Parties in writing.  <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Stock Sale Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p>On this the [____] day of the month of [_____________], in the year [______], [ABC TECHNOLOGIES] and its <br/>founders and the purchaser [JAMES INVESTSALOT], agree to the following:  <br/></p>
<p>Each undersigned purchaser and [ABC TECHNOLOGIES] agree to the purchase of [_____] shares in the <br/>company [ABC TECHNOLOGIES] at the price of $[Amount] per share. The purchasers agree to the price of <br/>$[PRICE] per stock at the Closing of the Company and its founders. Any shares purchased after this <br/>agreement, or additional shares, shall be purchased at the same above-stated price. <br/></p>
<p>The purchase of the shares shall be made by [JAMES INVESTSALOT] residing at [JAMES INVESTSALOT&#8217;S <br/>ADDRESS], by the day of [_____] in the month of [____________________], in the year [_________], or at <br/>another time agreed upon by both the company and the purchaser. Payment shall be made in the form of <br/>[___________________] to [ABC TECHNOLOGIES] located at [ABC TECHNOLOGIES&#8217;S ADDRESS]. The <br/>payment should be made to the bank of [BANK NAME], located at [BANK&#8217;S ADDRESS], in the account <br/>numbered [ACCOUNT NUMBER] routing number [ROUTING NUMBER]. <br/></p>
<p>The purchase of the stocks shall be finalized by the [____] day in the month of [________________], in the <br/>year [_______], at [__:____] [PM/AM]. <br/></p>
<p>The purchaser, [JAMES INVESTSALOT], holds the right to close his stock option and dissolve his shares of <br/>[ABC TECHNOLOGIES] at any time after the initial purchase date. [ABC TECHNOLOGIES] agrees to this <br/>stipulation. <br/></p>
<p>[ABC TECHNOLOGIES] notes that any purchase of stocks and shares of their company is an investment that <br/>has risks and losses associated. [ABC TECHNOLOGIES] notes that any purchaser undersigned is investing of <br/>their own free will, and understands the risks associated with purchasing stock in a company. The purchasers, <br/>by signing below, state their full knowledge of the risks associated with stock purchases, and sign this <br/>agreement of their own free will. This document does not stipulate the responsibilities of the Company, <br/>Purchasers, and Founders. <br/></p>

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b> <br/>Stock Subscription Agreement <br/></b></p>
<p>The undersigned agree to the purchase of stocks in the company [LMNOP PRODUCTIONS], located at <br/>[LMNOP PRODUCTIONS&#8217; ADDRESS], hereby known as The Company. [A TO Z INVESTMENTS], located at <br/>[A TO Z INVESTMENTS&#8217; ADDRESS], hereby known as The Purchaser, agree to the purchase of [______] <br/>shares in the Company at the initial cost of $[Amount] per share. <br/></p>
<p>The Company agrees to the purchase of this, a [_____]% shareholding. The Purchaser agrees to the purchase <br/>of this, a [_____]% shareholding. <br/></p>
<p>The undersigned agree to the following conditions of this [AGREEMENT]: <br/></p>
<p>The Purchaser shall pay $[AMOUNT] for the purchase of [_____] shares at $[RATE PER SHARE] per share. <br/>The payment is to be made to [LMNOP PRODUCTIONS] by the date of [____] in the month of [__________], <br/>in the year [______]. The payment is to be made to the bank [BANK NAME], located at [BANK ADDRESS], <br/>with the account number of [ACCOUNT NUMBER] and the routing number of [ROUTING NUMBER]. The <br/>payment is to be made by [__:____ PM/AM] by the above-stated date. <br/></p>
<p>The Company acknowledges the [_____]% shareholding as a commitment to further financial support. The <br/>Purchaser acknowledges the following expectations pertaining to a [_____]% shareholding: Voting on <br/>company policy, cooperation with the Company&#8217;s Board of Directors, conditional communication with the <br/>Company&#8217;s chief executive officer and chief financial officer. <br/></p>
<p>The Purchaser, by signing below, acknowledges that the Company is purchasing these stocks of their own free <br/>will. The Purchaser and The Company fully understand the risks and losses associated with the purchasing of <br/>stocks and shares of any company. The closing of the stock shall be permitted at any time after the initial <br/>purchase. The closing price of the stock will be a minimum of $[Amount] per share or as determined by the <br/>market price of the stock. <br/></p>
<p>The undersigned agree to all of the above-mentioned terms and conditions of this agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>[LMNOP PRODUCTIONS]: <br/></b></p>
<p>Representative Name:  <br/></p>
<p>Title:  Email:  <br/></p>
<p>Date of Birth:  Telephone:  Fax:  <br/></p>

<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>SUBCONTRACTOR AGREEMENT <br/>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Subcontractor Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into on <br/>________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between ________________________, <br/>with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Subcontractor&#8221;</b>) and <br/>________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <br/><b>&#8220;Contractor&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be automatically renewed <br/>for a new term. <br/></p>
<p><b>SERVICES PROVIDED <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Subcontractor agrees to provide the services listed below (hereinafter referred to <br/>as the &#8220;<b>Services</b>&#8221;): <br/></p>
<p>1. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>2. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>3. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>4. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>5. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>6. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>7. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>8. ____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Services must be completed by <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>COMPENSATION  <br/></b></p>
<p><b> <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Contractor agrees to pay the Subcontractor an amount of ________________ for <br/>the Services provided by the Subcontractor set forth in this Agreement.  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>- The amount of the total cost of the Services is ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- An amount of ________________ will be provided at the signing of this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>- An amount of ________________ will be provided at completion. <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENT</b> <br/></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties agree that the final payment of the Services will be made within <br/>________________ days upon the completion of the Services set forth in this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the means of payment will be via <br/>___________________________________________________________________________<br/>__________________________________________________________________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>WARRANTY <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Subcontractor warrants the Services provided for a period of ________________ <br/>years against any possible defects in terms of materials and/or workmanship. <br/></p>
<p><b>INDEMNITY AND INSURANCE <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Subcontractor agrees to indemnify the Contractor as well as defend him/her and <br/>any affiliated entities and/or individuals, if any, from any claims that may arise from third <br/>parties that relate to the Subcontractor&#8217;s work.  <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that the Subcontractor will hold at least the minimum required insurance <br/>coverage related to Workers&#8217; Compensation, Commercial General Liability, and Automobile <br/>Liability. <br/></p>
<p><b>RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, the Parties agree that this Agreement is a subcontractor agreement where the <br/>Subcontractor is an independent contractor who provides the services hereunder. <br/></p>
<p>- Under no circumstances shall the independent contractor be considered an employee, <br/>representative, agent or partner.  <br/></p>
<p>- This Agreement does not create any other partnership between the Parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>EXCLUSIVITY </b> <br/></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that this Agreement is not an exclusive arrangement and that the Parties are <br/>entitled to enter into other similar agreements with other parties. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in the event that any of the following occurs: </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>1. Immediately, in the event that one of the Parties breaches this Agreement or one of the <br/>conditions set forth in this Agreement and does not amend them within a period of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing a written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement <br/>shall be submitted to arbitration/mediation/negotiation (circle one) in accordance with, and <br/>subject to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>

c[1])break}g=f-1;0>g&&(g=0);var g=h[g].page,k=g.clientWidth,f=g.clientHeight,l=g.offsetLeft+g.clientLeft,m=c[0]-l;0>m?m=0:m>k&&(m=k);k=g.offsetTop+g.clientTop;c=c[1]-k;0>c?c=0:c>f&&(c=f);for(f=0;f<d;++f)h[f].rescale(a);b.scrollLeft+=m/e*a+g.offsetLeft+g.clientLeft-m-l;b.scrollTop+=c/e*a+g.offsetTop+g.clientTop-c-k;this.schedule_render(!0)},fit_width:function(){var a=this.cur_page_idx;this.rescale(this.container.clientWidth/this.pages[a].width(),!0);this.scroll_to(a)},fit_height:function(){var a=this.cur_page_idx;

</span></div><div class="t m0 x2 h4 y36 ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-<span class="ff3"> <span class="_ _0"> </span></span>Under <span class="_ _9"> </span>no <span class="_ _9"> </span>circumstances the Parties.<span class="ff5"> </span></div><div class="t m0 x2 h5 y39 ff1 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">EXCLUSIVITY <span class="ff2"> </span></div><div class="t m0 x2 h4 y3a ff2 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-<span ===== Sublease-Agreement-Template-Signaturely (1).html =====
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">
<html><head><title></title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
</head>
<body>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>SUBLEASE AGREEMENT <br/>PARTIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Sublease Contract Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Agreement&#8221;</b>) is entered into <br/>on ________________ (the <b>&#8220;Effective Date&#8221;</b>), by and between ________________________, <br/>with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Subtenant&#8221;</b>) and <br/>________________, with an address of ________________, (hereinafter referred to as the <br/><b>&#8220;Sublessor&#8221;</b>) (collectively referred to as the <b>&#8220;Parties&#8221;</b>). <br/></p>
<p><b>PREMISES <br/></b></p>
<p>- The premises that are to be subleased are located at (address) ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>PAYMENT AND COSTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The monthly rent to be paid is ________________. It is to be paid before the first day of every <br/>month, so that the first rent payment is due on ________________. <br/></p>
<p>- The method of payment preferred by both parties is ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>UTILITIES <br/></b></p>
<p>- Hereby, both parties agree that the Subtenant is responsible for paying  all the utilities or other <br/>charges associated with the Premises. <br/></p>
<p><b>DEPOSIT <br/></b></p>
<p>- Prior to taking the occupancy of the premises, the Subtenant will pay the Sublessor an amount <br/>of ________________ as a security deposit to cover the cost of any damages suffered by the <br/>premises and cleaning. Such security deposit will be returned to the Subtenant upon the end of <br/>this Agreement, provided that the premises are left in the same condition as prior to the <br/>occupancy. <br/></p>
<p><b>INSURANCE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Subtenant is to arrange renter&#8217;s insurance that meets the minimum standards required <br/>under the Sublessor&#8217;s original lease. <br/></p>
<p><b>TERM <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be effective on the date of signing this Agreement (hereinafter referred <br/>to as the &#8220;<b>Effective Date</b>&#8221;) and will end on ________________. <br/></p>
<p> <br/></p>
<p>- Upon the end of the term of the Agreement, this Agreement will not be automatically renewed <br/>for a new term. </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p><b>TERMINATION <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement may be terminated in the event that any of the following occurs: <br/></p>
<p>1. Immediately, in the event that one of the Parties breaches this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p>2. At any given time by providing written notice to the other party ________________ days <br/>prior to terminating the Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>DISPUTE RESOLUTION <br/></b></p>
<p>- Any dispute or difference whatsoever arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall <br/>be submitted to Arbitration/mediation/negotiation (circle one) in accordance with, and subject <br/>to the laws of ________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>GOVERNING LAW <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <br/>________________. <br/></p>
<p><b>SEVERABILITY <br/></b></p>
<p>- In the event that any provision of this Agreement is found to be void and unenforceable by a <br/>court of competent jurisdiction, then the remaining provisions will remain in force in <br/>accordance with the Parties&#8217; intention. <br/></p>
<p><b>ENTIRE AGREEMENT <br/></b></p>
<p>- This Agreement contains the entire agreement and understanding among the Parties hereto <br/>with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, <br/>inducements and conditions, express or implied, oral or written, of any nature whatsoever with <br/>respect to the subject matter hereof. The express terms hereof control and supersede any course <br/>of performance and/or usage of the trade inconsistent with any of the terms hereof.  <br/></p>
<p><b>AMENDMENTS <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties agree that any amendments made to this Agreement must be in writing, where they <br/>must be signed by both Parties to this Agreement.  <br/></p>
<p>- Accordingly, any amendments made by the Parties will be applied to this Agreement. <br/></p>
<p><b>SIGNATURE AND DATE <br/></b></p>
<p>- The Parties hereby agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and such is <br/>demonstrated by their signatures below: <br/></p>
<p>  </p>

</div></div>
<div style="page-break-before:always; page-break-after:always"><div><p>SUBTENANT <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>SUBLESSOR <br/> <br/>Name:____________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Signature:_________________________ <br/></p>
<p>Date:_____________________________ <br/></p>
<p> </p>

</div></div>
</body></html>

e=c.getBoundingClientRect(),c=[b.clientX-e.left-c.clientLeft,b.clientY-e.top-c.clientTop];a.rescale(Math.pow(a.config.scale_step,b.detail),!0,c)}},!1);window.addEventListener("keydown",function(b){var c=!1,e=b.ctrlKey||b.metaKey,h=b.altKey;switch(b.keyCode){case 61:case 107:case 187:e&&(a.rescale(1/a.config.scale_step,!0),c=!0);break;case 173:case 109:case 189:e&&(a.rescale(a.config.scale_step,!0),c=!0);break;case 48:e&&(a.rescale(0,!1),c=!0);break;case 33:h?a.scroll_to(a.cur_page_idx-1):a.container.scrollTop-=
a.container.clientHeight;c=!0;break;case 34:h?a.scroll_to(a.cur_page_idx+1):a.container.scrollTop+=a.container.clientHeight;c=!0;break;case 35:a.container.scrollTop=a.container.scrollHeight;c=!0;break;case 36:a.container.scrollTop=0,c=!0}c&&b.preventDefault()},!1)},rescale:function(a,b,c){var e=this.scale;this.scale=a=0===a?1:b?e*a:a;c||(c=[0,0]);b=this.container;c[0]+=b.scrollLeft;c[1]+=b.scrollTop;for(var h=this.pages,d=h.length,f=this.first_page_idx;f<d;++f){var g=h[f].page;if(g.offsetTop+g.clientTop>=
c[1])break}g=f-1;0>g&&(g=0);var g=h[g].page,k=g.clientWidth,f=g.clientHeight,l=g.offsetLeft+g.clientLeft,m=c[0]-l;0>m?m=0:m>k&&(m=k);k=g.offsetTop+g.clientTop;c=c[1]-k;0>c?c=0:c>f&&(c=f);for(f=0;f<d;++f)h[f].rescale(a);b.scrollLeft+=m/e*a+g.offsetLeft+g.clientLeft-m-l;b.scrollTop+=c/e*a+g.offsetTop+g.clientTop-c-k;this.schedule_render(!0)},fit_width:function(){var a=this.cur_page_idx;this.rescale(this.container.clientWidth/this.pages[a].width(),!0);this.scroll_to(a)},fit_height:function(){var a=this.cur_page_idx;
this.rescale(this.container.clientHeight/this.pages[a].height(),!0);this.scroll_to(a)},get_containing_page:function(a){for(;a;){if(a.nodeType===Node.ELEMENT_NODE&&a.classList.contains(CSS_CLASS_NAMES.page_frame)){a=get_page_number(a);var b=this.page_map;return a in b?this.pages[b[a]]:null}a=a.parentNode}return null},link_handler:function(a){var b=a.target,c=b.getAttribute("data-dest-detail");if(c){if(this.config.view_history_handler)try{var e=this.get_current_view_hash();window.history.replaceState(e,
"","#"+e);window.history.pushState(c,"","#"+c)}catch(h){}this.navigate_to_dest(c,this.get_containing_page(b));a.preventDefault()}},navigate_to_dest:function(a,b){try{var c=JSON.parse(a)}catch(e){return}if(c instanceof Array){var h=c[0],d=this.page_map;if(h in d){for(var f=d[h],h=this.pages[f],d=2,g=c.length;d<g;++d){var k=c[d];if(null!==k&&"number"!==typeof k)return}for(;6>c.length;)c.push(null);var g=b||this.pages[this.cur_page_idx],d=g.view_position(),d=transform(g.ictm,[d[0],g.height()-d[1]]),
g=this.scale,l=[0,0],m=!0,k=!1,n=this.scale;switch(c[1]){case "XYZ":l=[null===c[2]?d[0]:c[2]*n,null===c[3]?d[1]:c[3]*n];g=c[4];if(null===g||0===g)g=this.scale;k=!0;break;case "Fit":case "FitB":l=[0,0];k=!0;break;case "FitH":case "FitBH":l=[0,null===c[2]?d[1]:c[2]*n];k=!0;break;case "FitV":case "FitBV":l=[null===c[2]?d[0]:c[2]*n,0];k=!0;break;case "FitR":l=[c[2]*n,c[5]*n],m=!1,k=!0}if(k){this.rescale(g,!1);var p=this,c=function(a){l=transform(a.ctm,l);m&&(l[1]=a.height()-l[1]);p.scroll_to(f,l)};h.loaded?
c(h):(this.load_page(f,void 0,c),this.scroll_to(f))}}}},scroll_to:function(a,b){var c=this.pages;if(!(0>a||a>=c.length)){c=c[a].view_position();void 0===b&&(b=[0,0]);var e=this.container;e.scrollLeft+=b[0]-c[0];e.scrollTop+=b[1]-c[1]}},get_current_view_hash:function(){var a=[],b=this.pages[this.cur_page_idx];a.push(b.num);a.push("XYZ");var c=b.view_position(),c=transform(b.ictm,[c[0],b.height()-c[1]]);a.push(c[0]/this.scale);a.push(c[1]/this.scale);a.push(this.scale);return JSON.stringify(a)}};
pdf2htmlEX.Viewer=Viewer;})();
</script>
